Item_Response: Once there was a boy who was very lonely. His name was Noah. His mom realized he was very lonely, so she bought him a remote-controlled robot. Although it was very expensive, it was all worth it. The robot and Noah became best friends.           Noah wondered for a whole week of what to name his new robot, and on the last day, he named his robot Taylor. Taylor could do anything, she would supply herself full of many different types of food, she could play music, she could talk, and also was water-proof.           One day, Noah was walking home from the Thrift Store, he got a boat-load of toys, clothes, and he even got a chair. Taylor was so excited for when he came home, but suddenly saw his friend, Lauren. Taylor was not happy seeing him with another girl. She got feruste and rolled down stairs and stopped right in front of her.'What is this big pile of metal junk?' asked Lauren. Taylor got so mad that she tripped Lauren right as she was walking a way. Lauren got up and ran as fast as she could down the street. Taylor was pretty happy for her success, but Noah wasn't happy at all.             Noah relized Taylor was getting a little too protective over Noah. Noah told his mom and she said 'well we can't do anything, unless we return her.' Noah wasn't happy, he loved Taylor and didn't want to, but she was creeping Noah out. So, the next day, Noah and his mom went to the store and tryed to return her, but they wouldn't take her back. Noah and his mom went home still with Taylor. He went straight up to bed and fell a sleep.            The next day, he woke up and saw she was GONE!!! 'Oh no, where is she?' Noah spoke. He walked down stairs and noticed a oil trail. He followed it to the basement. He walked into the basement and saw she had busted. He was shoked and sad. He wondered how but knew it was for her own good.                                                                The End.

Item_Response: There are many different types of robots that can help a lot people when injured, and in need of food supplies. The Gemini-Scout, Dante 2, Mr. Gower, and the Angribots are very helpful robots.       One type of a helping robot is the Gemini-Scout. The Gemini-Scout is a remote controlled robot that does research and rescue work in mines underground. This robot may be small but it is extremely strong, it could carry food, water, and other sorts of supplies. The Gemini-Scout robot gathers information from any place it goes.                Another sort of robot is the Dante 2. The Dante 2 has a very interesting job. It climbs into active volcanoes to gather information for a scientist to study. This robot has eight legs, which help it climb the steep walls of the volcanoes. Dante 2 searches for vents, or holes, in the crater to collect any information about the gases that come out of it.                The next robot would be Mr. Gower. This robot is very helpful in hospitals, it helps doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Mr. Gower can go anywhere in the hospital, it can ride elevators, steer through hallways, and move around things that get in its way. Mr. Gower is alsoable to speak, and it does work that doctors and nurses used to do.                The last robot is the Angribot. The Agribot is a fruit picker, it might pick berries, oranges, grapes, or apples. Picking strawberries is a difficult job so, farmers have the Angribot to pick the strawberries. In Japan there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of a strawberry, and this helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.                 All these four robots have a different special job that is helpful to us. The Gemini-Scout, Dante 2, Mr.Gower, and last of all the Angribot.

Item_Response: The lab was pure white not a smudge of dirt on the ground or dust in the courners, all was perfect.The man in the white coat walked briskly down the hall.He had pale white skin and hair as black as midnight, the name Dr.Montage was printed on an ID card that was secured to his pocket.Dr.Mountage came to a door and scanned the ID card under the handle.The door opened and he walked in. Inside was a table and a body shaped mass under it.Hundreds of cords conected it to millions of michiens.He took off the tarp that conceled the large mass.Under it  was a shiny, metal body.It was the form of a boy, but made of metal.printed on its wrist where shiny gold inscription:   Project 1        001FRHOTP   'Finaly' Dr.Montage breathed 'three years and i'm done'.He smiled and prest a button that said REVIVE. But then, something went wrong.                 Jay Dill was a good boy and bright.He had short brown hair and and light skin,but there was one thing that was different about him than the other girls and boys; his eyes were the color of shiny metal.They almost glowed! Other than that Jay thought he was quite normal. Sadly, that changed one day.   Jay sat on the porch, siping lemonade.It was another hot afternoon in michigan,and Jay was spending his time relaxing, after working in the house the whole day he decided to rest.His mom came out then. ''Jay its time to do youre homework' she called.Mrs.Dill was just like her son, same brown hair and light skin exept her eyes were a bright green.'Come on' she said 'get youre homework done then you can play outside all you like'.Jay was about to get up but then a deep rumbeling sounded.Jay and his mother froze, then it stoped. 'Must have been an earth trem- WHAT THE HECK IS THAT!!!'   she screamed.Jay trurned his head to see but then there was a searing pain in his arm,a click in his brain and then everithing went dark.

Item_Response: 'Screechhhhh.' The sound was unbearable. It was annoying, and unknown.              It was around 3 a.m., California time. So it was 6 a.m. Michigan time. It was a chilly, windy night here in California. No one ever thought what would happen after this night. The family woke with a start. They went downstairs, and were expecting so see some kind of monster, but no. They saw a nearly identical robot of R2-D2. Was this a dream? It certainly was. It felt real though.            The robot was bowing to us - like we were some Greek God. It said 'I am here to help you with anything.' This was getting creepy. A robot that just appears at night and expects us to give him chores. Then the robot said 'Amelia, I know things have been tough for you, managing all the chores at home while Ben is working full time. Thats why i'm here, to help you with the chores and you can cherish the weather or your garden.' My mom and dad nearly fainted. Their faces gto as pale as a ghost. This was clearly not a dream. But it's really suspicious how a robot from who knows where just appeared at 3 in the morning. He could at least have better timing.         My mom replied very strictly. 'Whereever you came from, the back doors right down that hallway. Turn around and get out. We don't need you.' I was very surprised to hear something like that from my mother. Just as the robot was going to answer my dad picked the robot up, but it wouldn't budge. I think it might've super-glued himself to the ground. 'You need me. I need you. It's as simple as that.'                                  <><><><><><><><><><><>             Over the next few weeks, the robot, which doesn't really have a name was helping with anything. Dishes, laundry, watering plants and even cooking. He even offered me to change into my pajamas. I said no. Truth is, it was nice and better having the robot around. He would help with anything you need. We never asked any questions about how he got here or what his past was like. But man, he sure was good. Mom was so less stressed out and dad never got angry. It was paradise at home. Everything isn't perfect. Except for this. This whole arrangement was perfect.               Then something terrible happened, an exaxt year later, at 3 a.m. The robot left. No note, or heads up. After that, for some reason everything got better. Not worse like it normally is with mom, dad and I. It got better. Everyone did their fair trade of chores. No more yelling or stressing out. I felt like the rbot was somewhere in the house, helping us in invisibility. But how? Thr robot was gone and never was coming back. Probably going to another family to help them with their problems. But that didn't matter. the only thing that did was that the robot was here for one year exactly and he helped us with every single problem. To financial problems to getting a B- on a test. We knew the robot wasn't dead or even hurt. It was probably a thing my dad ordered to help - like a time share. A time share robot? I don't think those are invented yet. That would be something cool to invent though. Whatever it came from, a time share agent or even just spontaneiously it was real good.          *Snoreeeee* That dream was probably the best dream ever. Why? Because the dream came true.

Item_Response: Fiction story                 Think, what would you do if a robot came alive? Would you freak out and run, would you try and see if it's nice or mean or would you try and kill it? You see you don't only want to know these things you want to figuire out what you would do if it happened to you. For me I would freak out but at the same time I would be calm. But here is a story of how a robot came from so mean to a persons best friend.                             A long time ago there was a girl named Patrisha she was funny, smart and beautiful. Not many people knew her secret but most people did. She was known as The Robot Girl she didn't just know how to tame robots she knew how to sct to robots. So one day Patrisha went outside to see what's going on in her garage. As she got there she found cans, glasses, and a bunch of other stuff on the ground as she looked up she saw the most terrific thing she has ever seen.                 A Robot                The robot looked very mean and vicious with the silver metal and the gleaming red eyes staring right at her. Now this robot wasn't like the others. This one was built like a human. Patrisha freaked out at that time. She ran inside knowing that the robot was following. Right then she froze turned around to see the robot standing right infront of her. She held her hand up and so did the robot. Hand to hand she figuired out that the robot wasn't mean it was friendly and was only looking for a friend. The only hard part was that the robot doesn't know how to treat a friend.           So to start off she brought the robot into her bedroom and had it sit right on her bed. Once the robot was settled in she started talking. The robot looked confused and threw a lamp off the shelf hitting the floor and it shattered. So she thought maybe talking wasn't the robots thing and instead games were. They tried a bunch of games but none of them worked except one. It was the game SORRY the robot got so interested in how you could put the little piece back in it's home. The only thing is how do I comunicate with it? So she put her thinking cap on and started listing some ideas. In total she had 40 ideas so she went down the list.           Number one did not work and so on to ten. NOTHING!! She was getting so confused on why the robot wasn't doing anything she wanted it to do. So she went from ten to twenty. No results. Patrisha just about had it so she thought before giving up she should at least finish the list. Twenty to thirty. You know what I don't think I can do this anymore maybe I should just call someone to take the robot back to where it belongs. So she looked at the list one more time anf said. WAIT!! I want to try forty.           So she went straight to the robot and did number forty and there was no response so she started walking away when all of a sudden. HI!! MY NAME IS ROBOT 201 THANK YOU FOR FIXING ME!! I HAVE HAD A LOT DONE TO TRY AND GET ME TO TALK BUT NOW THAT I CAN TALK WOULD YOU LIKE TO BE MY FRIEND?       UH!! I don't know the way you were acting before was... was...       OH I JUST ACT THAT WAY BECAUSE ME NOT KNOWING HOW TO TALK IS ME NOT KNOWING WHAT YOU SAY. SO I NEVER UNDERSTOOD WHAT YOU SAY!!       Oh so I cured you? said Patrisha.       NOT ONLY THAT YOU TAMED ME!!           Patrisha was so happy that she gave the robot a hug and since then that robot has been her BEST FRIEND becuase everyone who doesn't know her story thinks she's crazy. That is Patrisha's story.

Item_Response: Chapter 1                                           Meeting the robots                  When you are a robot in a human's world it can be hard. The name's Bob. I guess my creator wasn't in his right mind when he named his creation but things like that just tend to happen.              I don't have a battery that needs to recharge at night like my other robotic friend but I run on food. Real food. I doubt you'll want to hear about my basic eating habits so I'll get on with the story. It all started in Michigan at Ernie's workshop with a hammer, some nails and a bunch of scraps of metal. That's what Ernie my creator used to build me. He had never had a child and was in his early sixties when he was offered the job of being an engineer. He was in good shape and he loved his work. By the end of his second year he started building robots. One of them is my 'twin brother' and is named Billy. Who names two robots Billy and Bob? Anyway. By the time he was 67 years old he had finally made another robot. Me. It was a total success. I was and still am the most sophisticated robot man has yet made. I get energy on food, my lips move when I talk and I grow the older I get. Ernie made my growth rate the same as an average human so I could fit in when I went to school, but did I fit in? No, I never did. I was just a metal scrap which had been animated and morphed.               About ten years after he created me he moved away and forgot all about me and Billy and this is the story of how we found him.                                                                                     Chapter 2                                                    The Search Begins            One morning in the middle of May I went downstairs to unplug Billy from the charger and wake him up. Then I had breakfast while Billy got his school stuff ready. Then it hit me.'Billy, where's Ernie?'. 'No clue.' Was the answer I got from him. When I went to check if Ernie had accidentally had sleeped in. He wasn't there, instead there was a heap of metal. I knew what it was. It was the same thing he put into me when he had created me. The battery. The special feature about that one is it charges itself. There was a note right by. It read 'I'm sorry I left without you two but the police officers wouldn't let me take robots onto a plane. By the time you read this I will most likely be in Toronto, Canada. And put that rechargeable battery into Billy.'            It took him all day to finally put the battery into Billy. They knew Ernie's 'secret' stash of money and by some miracle there were 200$ left untouched. They stared at each other and knew what they had to do.             By the next day we found ourselves in a tent eating rations. Actually only Bob ate them. Thankfully we were robots and Ernie had only made one mistake when he made us. We had no energy limit. All we had after a week was a knife, some food, a tent and a bow we had made and 67$. We had no idea how long it would take us to find Ernie but we knew it would be a while. But we didn't know it would take us as long as it did though. And that is how our journey began.                                                          Chapter 3                                                   RUN!!!!                         It had been almost two weeks since we had left and we still hadn't encountered any problems. While Billy scouted ahead I had to stay back at camp and make arrows with the knife. For self defense of course. By the time I had finished my third arrow I heard a growl. I had no idea what that was so I just went back to work. That was my greatest mistake, because seconds after a large grizzly bear broke through the bramble and charged me. I had just enough time to recover from shock to get out of the way. I picked up the bow and one arrow. I drew it and fired. I missed the bear. The angry grizzly charged again. I jumped out of the way and fired a second arrow. It missed. Then the real problem happened. Two more bears came and charged. My first thought was 'I'm doomed'. I closed my eyes. Nothing happened. I turned around and there were a pack of wolves running away. I packed my bag and ran without bothering to retrieve my arrows that had nudged into a tree.           It wasn't untill late at night that I found Billy. He had wondered where I had been. I was too lazy to say much. 'It involved three bears and a pack of wolves.' That was all I said untill next morning.                                                           Chapter 4                                               The wolves are back                    It was friday, August 13 when things went bad. It started with howling noises in the middle of the night. Billy came running into the tent and started packing up as fast as he could. I didn't need to ask questions because the howling had already answered them. I started packing too.               We had been running from and dodging wolves as they jumped at us. I had made lots of arrows and had been practicing with them. Three of the wolves had already stopped and turned around from injuries but a bunch of them still were on us. A minute later we emerged from the forest that had so far been protecting us and we found ourselves in front of a sign that said Welcome to Toronto. The wolves had turned around and given up when they saw what laid ahead of them. The city was marvelous to my eyes and I asked around if anyone knew of an old man named Ernie. We got lucky. Within the next day we were sitting next to ernie having a nice family reunion. Ernie had finally made a coat of skin and other stuff to help me look like a real boy. I was now proud of myself and felt like life was not as bad as it seemed anymore. Life is good.

Item_Response: One day, a robot suddenly started to drive after it had been transported to a local dump. I was so surprised, it must had been years since it last worked!     I did not know what to do with it, maybe I could keep, should I give it back to the creator.     It looked like Google's robot car and I was wondering why somebody would through that away? The robot seemed really dirty and dusty, so I decided to wipe it off a little, it also smelled like a oil leak, which made the robot sticky for when I wiped all the grim off.     Luckily my Mom and Dad put the trash in a trailer, so we were able to put it in their. I was barley able to convey them to bring it home with us, but I said 'Please, we should really find the creators, that makes it in California.'      The next day, we contacted the Google company to arrange a time when they can come to our house to pick up the robot. We left it outside, so it would be easy to get it in the back of the truck that the Google company was bringing.      Later that day, the truck was at our house. They had a thick rope to pull it and a fork lift to pull the rope, that was attached to the robot. Once they were finished, they said 'Thank you and we will be able to restore it.'      I was so excited that I found it and I wonder what it will look like restored?

Item_Response: There was a family who did not know but soon their future would change forever. Maya, a very intelligent 8 year old who loved to draw and invent robotic instuments never could get anything she tried to work right. Jack, age 11 who was also smart loved to help her firgure out how to get it to work. As much as they tried it would never work. But soon it would all change.                   The drafting of their next robot was almost done with all of their supplies ready to make the new robot. It was going to be able to do all of their chores and homework so they would have more time to work in the lab. It would also bring them food and water so they would not have to take a break from working. They each wanted their own so they could do work for each of them.                    It took at least three years of planning and creating to get their final product. It was finally the day to turn them on and they were really nervous that it would not work. They switched the switch on each of their robots but they did not turn on. They took the batteries out and charged them for another day. Then they put them back in their robots and plugged them in. Finally the robots turned on and Maya, and Jack could not believe they just build a robot that worked. It even did everything they wanted it to do. That would change their life forever.

Item_Response: ' Vanished'Said the scientist.   'The robot was here and now it is not.It is not my imagination this really happen'   'Explain it one more time?'the police man asked.   'I do not know he was here last night and when I woke up he was gone'.'   The room went silent.   ' I know everyone thinks I am crazy but he is out there right now.'   'Now sir what does this 'robot' look like?'   'He is light blue with purple and gold stripes.'   'Yes sir, and you said he had... super powers.' The police man tried to say professionally but could not do anything but laugh.   ' Mr. Police man sir, I understand that you think this could be a laughing matter but as far as I he could have run away.'   'So you are saying that he just... suddenly came a live.'   He said trying to hold down his laugh.   'Sir I know you do not believe in robots but trust me he is real.'   ' Okay sir'    ' He is like family to me.'    'So your 'robot' son ran away.'    ' I do not know.'    'I do not think we should waste police materials on your 'robot' son.'    'Sir do you have kids'    'Of course not. Kids are gross and mean and so much more.'    'Fine do not help.'The scientist grab his coat and out he went.        Other wise on the other side of town George the robot was to happy to have come to life.    George could clime on things and he could  run through water and the could also go into very hot things like volcanoes. But he just miserable. He was lonely and he was cold.    George wished he could go back to... Well, not being real.When it hit him... How was he alive. he wished the scientist was here so he could ask him but he was a long way away.    So he went out on a searcher for some clues leading to why he was like this.        'George' yelled the scientist       'George come home' he screamed again.    The scientist was tiered of searching for his little robot son.    But he did not want to give up so he search and search until...            George was trying very hard to find clues when he decided to go home.         'George.' he screamed    ' I miss you come home.' he said and cuddled up with a lamp post and fell asleep.'       While gorge was whipping around the corner to his house he saw the most bizarre thing he had ever seen.It was a idiot cuddled up with a lamp post. Then he realized that was his idiot. It was the scientist.        'George' the scientist called as he saw his robot.`           ' George how did you...:' you know I like you better this way he said as the walked to into  the sunrise home!

Item_Response: Maria looked to her right, she saw a garbage truck dumping loads of metal onto the landfill right next to her house. Every hour of the day garbage was being dumped into the landfill.         Maria had always been a only child. Even though she had lots of friends at school, she was always lonely at home. Maria needed a friend to keep her company at home, when her friends were a away. She needed someone to call a brother or sister. She needed someone to play with her after school. She needed a robot.         'That's it!' she thought 'I need a robot'. But how? How would Maria be able to make a robot, and with what would she make it with? Then she looked back at the landfill. She looked at the loads of metal that were dumped into the landfill. 'That's what i'll make it with!' exclamied Maria, 'I'll make it out of recycled metal'.         Maria ran to her house, opened her front door and slamed it shut, rushing to get to her phone to call up her best friend Sammi, so she could tell her the great ideas of how she was going make a robot. Maybe Sammi would even want to help her.'Hello?' said Sammi, answering the phone. 'Hi Sammi, it's Maria. I need you to come to my house imediately!' said Maria, hopping no stranger would take the metal that was in the landfill. 'Okay i'll be over in a bit' said Sammi, and they both hung up the phone.         'DING-DONG' the door bell had rang, it was Sammi. 'Hey Sammi! Come on in' said Maria, excited to tell Maria her big plan to make a robot. 'So why did you want me to come over so badly?' asked Sammi, and so Maria told her the brilliant idea on how she was going to make a robot. 'That's an awesome idea!' exclaimed Sammi. 'Well then, what are you waiting for? That's go get the metal and get to work!'         Maria's mother and father probably would not have liked that Maria was going to bring a load of old, used and rusty metal into their house, but Maria's parents were on a buisness trip in Japan to check out the new robot's this smart man made. So, she just hoped they wouldn't come home anytime soon. As soon as they had all the metal they needed (or thought they needed) they dumped it all on their kitchen table and started to brain storm ideas of how the robot look and how it would be made. Just incase you are wondering how in the world these girls are going to make a robot well, both of the girls parents work for companies who build robots. 'Okay, I think it should have a square body and a triangle head and be painted yellow' decided Sammi. 'No, no, no I think it should have a circle head and a egg shaped body and be painted white' explained Maria. 'Yeah that's a great idea!' exclaimed Sammi, so they decided to have a robot with a square head, an egg shaped body and be painted white.         After hours and hours of blood, sweat and tears, they had finished making the white robot. 'Maria I have a question' asked Sammi 'how are we exactly going to make this robot come to life?' Maria looked at her with a smile on her face. 'You'll see' said Maria. Maria suddenly jumped out of her seat and ran down into her dark, mysterious basement. 'What could possibly be in that basement that would make a robot come to life?' thought Sammi.         Sammi waited and waited but Maria never came out of the basement. Then suddenly a dark blue glow came out of the basement, and so did Maria. As Maria walked toward Sammi she held a small metal ball that glowed the color of dark blue. 'This' Maria said 'is what's going to make our robot come to life'.         She moved closer and closer to the robot and opened a metal flap by where the heart should be. She stuffed the metal, glowing ball into the flap and connected three wires to it. The whole robot started to shake, and the floor started to shake! And then everything stopped moving, and a little white robot started to fly through the air yelling 'Finally i'm alive!' Then it stopped moving and floated toward Maria 'thank you master you made me come to life'. 'Please, call me Maria' ordered Maria. Sammi stood speachless in the corner of the room. Then the phone rang 'Hello Maria?' spoke Maria's mother 'Hi Mom! You could not believe what just happened! I've got a new friend!' and Maria hung up the phone, so excited to play with her new robot friend, Marie.

Item_Response: Once upon a time there was a person name Steve who decided to make a robot. He decided to name the robot, Bob. Bob was a big robot who was made from parts that Steve found in a junk yard. Bob was rusty and dirty but Steve loved him. One day Steve was eating a hot dog and reading the news paper, When he heard a loud crash coming from his shed were he builds things. Steve ran and hid under his bed. 2 hours later Steve finally got anough courage to get out from his bed and go downstairs. He looked around but the only thing he saw was his cat, Muffin, eating lettuce, that Steve had dropped on the floor when he got scared. Steve decided to take Muffin with him and go see what made the raquet in his shed. Steve got to the shed and looked around, then gasped, Muffin passed out and fell out of Steves arms. There in the middle of the room was a hornet.       Steve ran as fast as he could and didnt stop until he was under his bed. 5 hours later it dawned on Steve that 1. he had left Muffin in the shed, and 2. that a hornet couldnt have made that much noise. So Steve went out to his shed and picked up Muffin who was still out cold, and looked around. He looked into the corner of the shed and did a double take.  The robot he created just for fun, and to try something differnet, was standing in the corner, its large eyes glowing a bright, blinding red. Steves eyes got as big as dinner plates, and the robot let out a loud       'Hello, hello hello hello'.       Steve opend his mouth but no words came out. Steve just stood there a expression of amusement and horror plastered on his face.           Later Steve found out that Bob came alive beacuse he mixed up some wires and he had came alive. Bob and Steve have done many fun things together and had some good memories. Steve takes Bob to the grocery store and to the amusment park, regular parks and on long road trips. Bob loves riding in the car and sticking his head out the window. Every 5 years on May 21st to May 28, Bob has to go to a special building with white walls and wall to wall white carpets, and alot of electric plugs and get charged for one week. Steve always misses Bob terribly, and treads that week. But when Bob comes home Bob is very exited and happy so they go to many different parks and places to try to get some energy out of him.           The fun didnt last on May 30, 3090 Steve got a terrible phone call. The people at Newchester (the charging place) always leave Bob in for 1 week only. If they are one minute late over a week Bobs knobs and weels and everything inside of him will melt. That is kind of saying that he dies. Well Martha, the kind lady incharge of Bob every five years, left Bob in the wall 1 minute and one second two long. So on June 4th 3090, Steve had a funeral for Bob.Steve went to say his last goodbye when suddenly Bobs eyes started glowing yellow and in a quiet but happy voice Bob said       'I feel better than I've ever felt'   and stood up and huged Steve.       Steve and Bob have lived happily in California ever since and now are even better freinds than before.

Item_Response: Once upon a time in a land filled of junk, there lived a gray, rusty, tin can named Tiny. Tiny was ignored, rejected and left out. All of the tin cans in Canville, had had arms and legs, ears and even had feet. They thought Tiny was different and weird, and not normal, so they never asked him to play. Everyday Tiny cried and cried about not looking the same as others, and not fitting in. HE could only dream about fitting in.   One day his dream came true.....                  A nice summer night in the middle of July, Tiny was getting ready to go to sleep when all of a sudden he felt a strange feeling.  A tiny blue light shined on his mound of trash, so bright that Tiny had to squint his brown, rusted eyes to see who was there, nobody was. 'Wow, that was weird,' he said to himself. 'What was that? 'Then Tiny heard a noise... 'ZZUUPPAA!!!!!!!' Poof! Tiny turned into a brand new shiny silver toy robot! Tiny couldn't believe it! His wish had come true, all he could ever want. He had mechanical arms and legs, a bionic inside, and his very own set of feet! Now Tiny could do anything his friends could, and have the most fun he could ever had! All of his friend excepted him, and apologize sincerely for being such bad friends. All Tiny could to was enjoy his new Robot figure by trowing a party for Canville. He used his mechanical arms and legs for putting up the streamers, his bionic insides to play amazing music, and he used his feet to rock the dance floor! The party was so great, all of Canville declared Tiny as the official party thrower robot.            And that's how Tiny became a Robot!

Our practice was going great and then theirs the sound again but this time I was hearing It from different parts of the gym but not At the same time.          Practice was just about over so coach let us out a little early and our whole team Went to where we heard the noise and then we went to the very top of the bleachers and I saw a silver Object flying towards me making that same sound and when It got closer I notice It's arms spread out and It pretty much just does a perfect tackle on me as I fall to the ground It stands up and I see that It's a robot.         I look at It everyone's surrounding me and this little robot. The robot just says hi my name is Spike. Everyone just stands there with there jaws dropped down to there legs and I was the only one to say hi back and the robot says, ''can I live with you.'' I don't know what else to say so I say sure and he just flies right out the door. My teammates haven't moved an inch still and I just follow him along.         That night we did nothing and whent right to bed. Spikewakes me up with a huge bacon and egg samwich wich was amazing but still no words. Then he said can we go for a walk and I said sure we were walking and then I saw a sign that said missing toy robot and the picture looked just like Spike and I said theres your house isn't It. He said I don't know but I wan't It to be. I knocked on the door and a little kid yelled Ssssssppppppppiiiiiiiiiikkkkkkkkkkkkeeeeeeeee and the gave eachother a big hug.                                                The end

Item_Response: Once upon a time there was a young boy named Fred, who just wanted to build a robot, but no one ever believed in him. Not his parents nor teacher. Not his bother or sister, all he wanted to do is be a scientist. And an engineer. But no one would believe in him just because he got bad grades. He just wanted to live his dream.       Though his best friend, who didn't believe in him either, he suggested Fred show his ability to build a robot, but he said it in a sarcastic grasp voice,       'You'll never be able to build a robot, but if you're so cocky about it why don't you show us your 'skills.' Than I'll belive you.'       So Fred has his work cut out for him. But he would do everything he had to just to show them he could live his dream. He took a ton of time just to make this robot, some time he even skipped school. Months later he came up with this brilliant idea to make a robot so he started from scratch and made a robot called Filly-dilly-bob-joe. He was an amazing robot he could do absolutely everything you asked him to do. And the best part about this story is that he was a best friend to a wonderful young man.        Filly-dilly-billy-joe's job was to be the maid of the house. He had to buy groceries, clean the floors and fold the clothes. Everything cleaning wise Fred didn't want to do. And the best part is that he only listens to Fred's command, therefor his siblings and parents can't use him because they were the ones who never believed in him.       His creation became a big hit and soon enough everyone had a robot in their home. All exept his family and friends, they couldn't buy one because they didn't believe him.       I feel pretty inspired by this story to not listen to anyone else and live your dreams.       Everyone should live their dreams.       Everyone.

Item_Response: One school day started off as a normal day, I woke up, ate breakfast, brushed my teeth, then rode the bus. That was when everything that could go wrong did, only to lead to an amazing find.       I got to school then while I was walking to class I slipped and all my papers scattered everywhere. While I was almost done picking them up, the first bell rang and everyone started running to their homeroom, scattering my papers even more. I thought, About 20 people ran past me and none offered to help. Sheesh! Talk about rude! I finally finished picking up my papers then started fast walking(not running so I won't slip) to homeroom when I walked inside everybody ran out of the room, going to their next class.       I shighed and started to walk to science and we had a... pop quiz! Guess what else! I failed. La, had to write a story about fish, my pen broke and all its ink spilled all over me, my desk and my paper. Math, I fell alsleep when Mr. Garbon started to talk about cubic centimeters only to wake up with everybody staring at me. Scocial Studies, We went to watch a video about indians and I started to daydream then Ms. Yen asked me a question and I had no idea that she was even talking! The rest of the day went on and on until I rode the bus home.       I shouted out, 'Mom, I'm home!' Then I found a note saying, Sorry darling, emergency conference. See you after! XOXO, Love Mom. I decided to do my homework outside. I went to my backyard and then I saw a robot in front of me lying in a big heap. Then,out of nowhere, a lightning bolt hit it! It wasnt even raining, and it was a nice sunny day. Then the robot came to life.       I screamed then ran behind a tree. I peeked out, curiosity getting the better of me, and the robot's hand turned into a broom and the other a duster and it was cleaning up our back porch. It must be a cleaning robot! ,I thought. I tiptoed over to it and took its arm and led it to my room and I'll admit, my room was a mess it started to clean and I shut the door. This is awesome! I can have it clean my room every day and it will be a lot easier to find all my things!       Mom came in right as I walked past the front door and I told her everything, the robot my terrible day and how we could keep it and have it be our maid, everything. She agreed and said that she was proud of me going through that day and said that life will be easier.

Item_Response: Nicole the cool robot!!                            Nicole is a very cool robot she can do whatever you tell her to but Nicole doesn't just do everything you say, and she loves to play but mostly she helps lots of elderly people and people who have mental problems and other conditions.                           If you are at home and you are very board, then Nicole is the perfect robot for you she can hang/play with you. Nicole can do many things such as play catch, transform into any animal you want and she can act like it.         She can even act your age, like a boy/girl teenager, adult, preteen, kid/child pretty much ant thing. Guess what she even has her very own home phone and CELL PHONE so you can call her and asks to hang, just don't forget she helps elderly/mental people so she might be busy!                          Now you can learn more about how Nicole works with helping elderly/mental people!!                  When Nicole is helps orderly/mental people she scans the so she can tell if they are sick or even have diabetes. If the person does she will take them to a hospital or even a doctor and she will tell the doctor what is going on with the elderly/mental person. Once Nicole is done explaining to the doctor the doctor will then take the elderly/mental person and do his or her business.                           When the doctor is done he/she will take the patient back to Nicole And Nicole will take he/she back to home safely and help another person and it repeats over and over again. THAT IS WHAT NICOLE IS LIKE!!!!!

I stood there paralized. Then the robot said i do whatever you would like.I told it to jump up and down and it did. So i told it to do other things and it listened.The next day i brought it to school and it started beating someone up but then the person just started beating the robot and it got smashed.I was so sad i just ran home to my room.Then i heard a knock.I opened the door and the robot was there! It said to me that it fixes itself.And even today i still play with him.                                                        THE END

Item_Response: Beep,beep,beep goes the flashing lights on my robots head. We are in my garage on this beauftiful summer day and I am checking to make sure he will still be able to function when I bring him to my first day of school. Suddenly as I am checking his head, a wire pops up and out of nowhere he starts rumbling. As quick as it started, it stopped but my sliver, metal, human like robot wasn't there anymore. He was replaced by an actual human! A boy with brown hair and dark blue eyes to be specific.             The rest of the week before school couldn't have possibly been any better! The robot, which I named Jimmy, turned out to be a search and rescue robot! He has told me may stories about some extremely dangerous search and rescues. For instance, one time he had to go as close to a volcano as anyone has ever gone a go a little bit farther! The only problem was my parents, what would I tell them? I decided that since Jimmy never needed anything that when it came time for school I would tell them I made him look like a boy so he would be more impressive!              Sadly on the last day before school we were playing in our boat on the Mississippi River when the current tipped us over! I heard a few shocks from Jimmy and then he was gone. Even though I told everyone the story at school they still didn't believe me and without any proof I knew they never would.

Item_Response: the robot           One right and sunny morning Geff Fiddlestcks was roming in the woods. He saw trees with brightly colored leaves, he saw squirlls hampering about, but one thing he saw surprised him. It was a robot. I'm not talking about those mini toy robots, but a giant real one. It was just lying there on the ground. He looked around it, he kicked it, he even smelled it and finally he dared himsef to touch it. It was hard and rusty. Cool he thought I wonedr if it runs on batteries? I could fix it! but just as he picked it up he heard a beeping sound, then all of a sudden it straighted up looked around and stretched. He walked toward Geff and just stood there with his hand out. Geff hesitated for a moment then shook it. Nice to meet you he said, do you have a name? The robot shook  his head. thats ok Geff said ill name u..... aha BoB. you can come to my house for supper I'm sure mother won't mind. So he led the robot to his house and was about to introduce him to his mother when all of a suddden.... SHREAK!!!!!! Geff get away from that that thing! yelled his mother. No mom you don't understand said Geff he's my friend. Suddenly his mother stopped Is he harmless? she asked. Yes said Geff he wanted to stay for supper his name is bob. he can talk? asked his mother. Well not exactly he just nods his head and points. Well then he can stay replied his mother go set the spare bed and come to the table your supper's cold.

Item_Response: One day on robot island a lady robot named Sythia had just married my dad Robert. Soon after they were married I came along. My name is Nick. I am 5ft wide and 4ft tall. When i'm all grown up all be as big as my mom, 10ft wide and 7ft tall. Alot of surprises of encountered since then though.                                                        Starting from day 1                I was a very tiny young one. I was only 2ft wide and 2ft tall. That's a very small robot for normal ones.I was born with a robot desiese called Rollaferbia. (Unable to properly wheel around on balance). But  i wasn't able to go to the robot children's hospital till I was over the age of 1 years old.Without a doubt after my amazing 1st birthday party full of  obstacle courses and lot's of present's I was brought to the hospital.I was brought to my bed and was brought to the surgical room. I was knocked out so I didn't know much but this is stories I heard from my great ol' grandmother.The bad news was that the procedure didn't  go well I lost one of my wheels and spreded the desiese to my arms. My parent's were'nt happy. They were really disapointed. That night whrn I finished my glass of chocolate milk and chocolate chip cookies i fell asleep in my bed. The next morning I woke up and the only person there was my grandmother was there  crying.Where are my parent's? At the lunch room? Went to grab something from home? Soon afterwards my grandmother told me. ' Sweedoms, I know this is going to be hard for you to understand but'. Small Pause. ' Your parent's won't beable to take care of you anymore and your going to live with me'. Tears were running down my eyes this can't be happening. But it turns out it was a true story.                                 Sweet ol' grams and a lot of rolling                        Over the next year or so I was in no sociallality or anything pesides my physical therapy. The ladies were nice there. Julie, Samantha, and Ivy. My favorite was Ivy. The other two are nice and helping but Ivy actually guides me through the process and does all my files. One time she was so worried about me she spent the night. I loved it there. I loved grams but every since the surgery she's been way over protective. It's not a big deal though, I know why she is, plus I see Ivy everyday. I kind of have a tinsey crush on her. She also always bakes a lot of cookies for me just like grams. Soon after another year and a half went by suddenly grams passed. I did'nt know what to say, she was my only connection to my family. It turns out she had a similar desises called wheelervy. Similar but it affects the whole body. Her theramal camera first broke down then the rest just stopped. I had to get put into the foster robot system. I was put there for 6 months , and at this point I wasn't aloud to go to physical therapy anymore which I was very bummed about. When I thought news can get any worse no joke Ivy , Ivy came and adopted me! I was so happy I couldn't even help but wheel to her and fall. She laughed. 'Nice try Nick time to get back to my place '. I was so syched I finally forgot everything that has happened to me and only focused on the future. Me and my mom Ivy's future.

Item_Response: LAX-17 is a small robot that scientists have built that is meant to teach and coach lacrosse. The LAX-17 has two mechanical arms and and treads intead of legs becauseif it didn't it would get stuck in the mud on those rainy days. The LAX-17 only weighs 64 pounds so it is pretty easy for a human to carry if needed.           The LAX-17 is capable of picking up a lacrosse stick and playing just like a pro. It also can give pointer to new people to the sport. Now lets say your out on the feild and your stick breaks well the LAX-17 can restring your stick, fix it, or just make you a new one any way you like.       So if your one of those people that is crazy about lacrosse then you should definetly gat a LAX-17.

Item_Response: PLANS:   scientists are in a lab, putting the final parts into place. they are trying to make artificial bodies for solving deformities, and in some models, for military and athletic purposes. they put a body in a robot body, but the emergency computer brain and the human brain battle each other for control of the motors and advanced sensors. eventually, the computer forces the human brain to surrender and another, non-computer controlled, bionic body fights the original into submission.       WRITING:                                   Two Brains, one Body           'Dr. Henton, the final motor circuits are in place, and testing is inevitable now' the lab assistant triumphantly proclaims. 'Great, we've already recruited testees for the A.A.M.B.' Dr. Henton replies, fingering the oily steel mechanics resting on the workbench. 'Now we'll bring in the experiment' he smoothly replies, buttoning his white lab coat.             Both nervous and excited, Nate Carpenter runs his hands through his long black locks, on his face, on his jeans, staring at the cieling lights, thinking 'this is the last time I'll ever feel these'.   The nurses' calming words do nothing to ease the waterfall of emotions of being the first to try inventions, a jumble of fear, excitement, nausea, and gratefulness for the privilege. The last thing he sees as a human is the nurses pulling anasthaesics out of the polished cabinets and giving him sleep medications.             Sixteen hours later, he wakes up to find his senses strangely acute, and his physical abilities strangely stronger. But, the oddest thing of all is that he felt another presence in his seven and a half foot tall body of steel. The scientists told him that there was an emergency computer brain that would take over if he went unconscious. They had surprised looks on their faces when he said he heard another, computerized voice in his head.             Another week later, he had a debate with half his body. He won, but it startled him. After a few more days of it, he was steadily getting more weary from his body growing more and more rebellious. He tried to reach the phone, which took immense concentration. But to his dismay, his hand swatted it away like a bug. The computer then spoke to him. 'You shall comply with all the rules and regulations set  by the Athletic Aerial Motorized Body. This includes dismantling any mental or physical uprising  by current organic being. Emotions are now banished by body regulations' droned the computer.             He then had any thought disappear, only capable of seeing and feeling. He would cry out if he had the ability to think about it. All he could is see what the computer could see, a iron fist grasp agonized faces, guns being fired, another robot clutch him, blackness. Then he could think again. He was alive again! After losing consciousness again, he was back in his organic body.

Item_Response: My name is Marcus Price, and I just built a spying robot for the U.S.A marines. The name of this awesome robot will be the otter bot.       'I will be up for dinner in a second.'' I yelled to my mom.''It is not about dinner honey, you have some serious company.'' she yelled at me. I ran up the stairs to find a man in a suit.sitting on the couch with a hummer in the drive way. '' Hello Marcus the man said with a smile on his face. ''We need to talk about something very serious.'' he said. I sat down on the couch next to my mom and said to him what is this about. ''My name is general Martin of the U.S.A marines. I would like to talk to you about a job that could change the war. At the tie we were at a war with North Korea and the U.S.A needed a technology upgrade.       ''Are you an inventor Mr.Price the general asked. ''Yes I am.'' i said cautiously. ''The marines have a job for you that could change your life forever. we need you to build a spying robot. ''Ok...'' I said. It is up to you how you want to make it but it needs to be strong and stelthy.'' he said. Me and my mom walked into the kitchen to talk about it and she said it was ok. ''I will do it.'' I said with a smile.       I sped down stairs to get to work right a way. I started thinking that it should be able to swim sense North Korea is surrounded by water. Then the idea hit me i would build a robot otter. it would be about 2 feet long and way about 30 pounds  and have all the characteristics of a real otter. it would have a tale,claws. and the ears and nose would be censers. So I got to work.       7 weeks later       Well i am done and it looks incredible! It looks just like a otter it even has fur and everything. it can swim, knows about 70 languages, is bullet proof and has night vision. I  turned it in to the marines and it is now in North Korea spying as we skeak now. One thing that the general didn't tell me was I got 1,000,000 dollars! now if you will excuse me I am in Hawaii and i have to catch a wave.

Item_Response: 'What does it do?'             'So far we do not know.'             'Then what is the point?'             'Well we programmed it to help the world, discover unknown things, make the world reveal whatever its hiding. Someone has to do it, but most of the journeys are too dangerous. People would die. We are positive this robot is loving, along with the characteristic of lovable. He is a very good crop collector, too.'             'Well, how do you know what this piece of junk does, it looks useless and it isn't even powered up.'             'Yes. That is the only thing left we are working on. Turning it on has been the greatest challenge yet. We have tried everything, it just seems like we did something wrong. But now, it is late. We can continue the conversation tomorrow.'             The scientist flicked the lights off and left the laboratory with his son.                                                  3,000 years later...                         'What is that over there by that old building?' asked Dr. Naureen. 'It's very shiny.'             'That looks like a robot,' shouted Dr. Barbknocker. 'Excavate it, we shall take it to the laboratory. C'mon, let's get to work.'             Later that evening, the scientist figured out a way to make the robot come to life! The thing needed a name and some major cleaning. The scientist named him Derek. They washed and oiled him, painted him in a nice dark green. He looked brand new! It took lots of time, but Dr. Barbknocker (the leader of the scientist) and some others found out what Derek could do. He could shrink to small sizes and fit into places the human thumb could never get. Derek discovers the unknown and is very careful with new objects.             He is also very caring, he loves children and animals. He can sing, dance and entertain. He is very useful for those in handicaps. He serves doctors so doctor may focuse on more important things. Derek is a plant lover just as much as he loves everything else. He helps farmers grow and collect fruits, vegetables and other crops.             Derek is loved and everlasting people praise, respect and protect this robot for all the goo deeds he has done to change the beloved world.

Item_Response: D-39               Way up high in the snowy Himalayas, there was a secret Chinese military base. The  leader there was Men-Ching, the Chinese dictator who was insane and was obsessed with having military domination of the entire world. Men-Ching and his team of scientists were almost done building their lifetime dream. . . . . . . . . D-39, a man-size robot designed to bring down the mighty U.S.                Meanwhile, in Washington DC, Anthony James, the president of the US was meeting with his army generals to discuss the current situation with China. 'OK,' said the president, 'today we are meeting to discuss our current situation with China.'             'I think we should capture Men-Ching and interrogate him to find out what is going on over there.' said Brad Wickman, the leader of the Marines. After some of the other generals stated their ideas, the president decided that the best course of action to take would be to send a small robot with a lot of microphones and cameras into the China through the Himalayas. That night, a B-2 bomber equipped not bombs, but the little robot, flew over Asia and dropped the little robot into the mountains. The robot fell approximately 2 kilometers away from the secret Chinese military base. The scientists watching the live video directed the robot toward a faint flicker of light up ahead. Soon, the robot reached the base and the fascinated scientists had it roll around the outside until it found a way to get in. The entrance just happened to be where D-39 was being stored. The scientists gasped as they saw the huge killer robot come to life and turned towards it. The robot fled quickly away, but the spy robots little treads were no match D-39's long legs. It quickly caught up to the little droid and blasted to bits with it's shoulder mounted Gatling guns. All of the Chinese scientists came running as fast as their fat little legs could carry them. When they got there, the saw the little pieces of metal on the floor along with some cameras and microphones. 'Oh no,' said one of the scientists, 'D-39, what happened?'   'This little spy entered the complex through my door and me killed it.' replied D-39 mechanically.   'So know the stupid Americans know of D-39. We must attack them right away.' said Men-Ching.             The next day, the first ever foreign attack on the continental US occurred. The Chinese dropped D-39 along with a thousand elite Chinese soldiers.With D-39 leading the attack, the Chinese easily took the unguarded city of Boston. Then, they made their big mistake they decided to stay the night outside of Boston. As the soldiers were sleeping, and D-39 was charging, the Americans bombed their camp with over 50 planes. Every soldier was killed except D-39, whose armor was so good that the bombs had not hurt him severely. His biggest injury was the rockets in his chest exploded when a bomb went of near him. When they blew up, they damaged part of him that kept him in contact with the Chinese and kept him loyal to them.              The next day, when a party of heavily armed US marines, lead by Sergeant Jacob Domalgski, went to see what was left of the Chinese camp. When they got their they found a confused D-39. The soldiers approached him and he didn't fire. He allowed the soldiers to put him on a stretcher and carry him back to their camp, from their, he was sent to the Pentagon where scientist repaired him and made him loyal to the US. The best thing by far they did to him though was gave him the ability to feel emotions and have a personality. As a thanks to the squad of Marines who had rescued him, D-39 asked the leaders if he could join there unit and they said it was fine. Exactly five days later the US, lead by D-39 captured and executed Men-Ching and started a democratic government in China. Finally, the world was at peace again. THE END.

Item_Response: It was a breezy automn day the sun was Very hot and the wind was blowing hard. Young Timothy green was trying to build a self manuvering robot. 'Timothy! youve been trying to make a sucsessful robot for 8 years are you ever gonna Give up?!' Timothy could feel a sarcastic reply about to burst out of his mouth but he decided not to reply with an attitude. 'Mom ive been working on this project for a very long time why cant you just support it?' Timothy replyed in a staggering voice. 'Well ive been trying to support it honey but youve been doing this for years!' 'Its driving me crazy!' Ohhh Timothy could feel an argument brewing in himself one that which his mother has never seen before. one more thing and he would snap. His mother replyed again but he just decided to ignore it. All through the night Timothy worked efforetsly on his Machine trying to figure out how to get it to work. Until suddenly it said One word 'Hello'. Timothy had been shocked! amazed he called  for his mother in excitment. 'Mom!' 'What' she replyed still mad from the arguement. 'It works my machine said something!!' 'Ok im coming but if this is a lie im gonna get even more mad.' she said sorley. As Timothys mom came down to the basement Timothy gently turned the machine off. 'Ok what is it?' Timothys mom was already down next to him staring at the heap of metal that was suspose to say something. Timothy Pressed the palm of his hand on the ON/OFF switch. He turned it on. The machine replyed with a cold arkward silence. Timothys mother said 'Is this a joke?' 'I have better things to do than sit here waiting for this peice of metal to actually say something.' Timothy replyed in an offended voice 'Hey!' 'It actually did say something! im not lieing!!' 'Yeah and pigs can fly' she replyed in a sarcastac voice as she went back upstairs. Timothy sat there in disapointment his hopes had boosted up a minute ago then another minute his hopes had went way down. In disgust he turned off his machine and went to bed. In Timothys dream he drempt of making a machine that could do all the basic things a human could do. Make food, do chores, e.t.c. But Timothy woke up before he was rewarded the best machine maker in the universe. moaning and grumpy Timothy got up and put some coffe beans in the coffe maker. When it was ready he put the whole brew of coffe and put it into a big mug. After his pleasent cup of bland coffe Timothy changed his cloths and drank the last sip of coffe he went straight to work. Right after going downstairs he heard his mother creeping down the basment doorway. 'What the heck are you doing up so early?!' She said sounding very irritaded. Impatiently Timothy replied 'Im working on my machine.' 'What!' 'Your working on that junk again!?' She said as she pounded up the basment stairs. Timothy whispered to himself agrivated now 'Well good morning to you to.' Timothy just couldnt figure out how he got the machine to say that! he considered rewiring it but that could take a week. 'hmm' he said curious   he wondered if he could make an outlit in his machine then transfer it to the computer and then control it from there. 'Ok i better get working on the outlit' Timothy said excitedly.   'Argg if only i can make the outlit big enough for the cord!' Finally after a hard 6 hours of trial and error he got the cord to fit. 'Ok now i need to set up a program into the computers mainframe and somehow transfer it into the machine.' Timothy decided after making the program he would name it Operation Robot. He made the program so when he typed a word in it would hopefully send it to the robots speakers he installed earlier. Before he could test his masterpiece out he had to instal a tiny little computer onto the robot to transmit the sounds to the speaker. He began on the computer around 8pm at night. He had dosed off around 4:00 AM in the morning. Groggy he woke up around 6:00 AM laying somehow on his workbench. Yet again he made himself some more bland coffe and quietly worked downstairs not to disturb the sleeping lion which his mother was. He turned on the lights downstairs and installed the computer into the robots chest. Then finally he installed the word program into the small computer. He turned the speakers up and booted up his computers. Quietly he walked over to his contraption turned it on slowly then sat down at his computer. Sweating very hardly now he slowly typed in 'Hello how may i help you master?' Then he pressed 'ENTER.' After he pressed that one button it changed his life forever. The robot replied exactly what he wanted it to say. he was dumbstruck after a few minutes of sitting there he jumped up out of his chair ran upstairs pulled the sleeping lion out of bed and brought her downstairs. he told her what he did then she tried the machine out by typing in some words. 'Amazing!!' 'This is incredible!' She said 'Thankyou now do you see what i was doing isnt usless at all?' Timothy said in a proud voice. 'Well you can get back to work' she said as she walked up the stairs. 'Wheres all of the coffe?' his mother asked from upstairs. 'Umm i dont know i dont drink coffe its disgusting.' 'Ok if you say so' his mother said suspiciously. Timothys mind was racing rapidly now if he could make his program do more things this could be even better! He was thinking 'I could make this robot do many more things from just the touch of a button!!' 'Moving, serving, doing simple tasks!' Now Timothy green just began his journey in making robots. The following year Timothy installed all the things he wanted the robot to do his dream had finally come true. After imaging robots and building them ever since he was in kindergarden he reached an amazing accomplishment. Then the next following year he was rewarded a Nobel prize for best invention and many other life achivment prizes. But when timothy was little and in school nobody supported his ideas and imagination so Timothy Green had no friends. And this robot had one simple name it was the name Timothy had kept in his head ever since he was little.'Friend'                                                                                                              THE END                                                                              (P.S hah had he shown them sincerely, Timothy Green).

Item_Response: The Robot Teacher                        The Robot Teacher is a robot that teaches children.   It is very smart. The Robot teacher needs to charge for 5   hours than it can stay up for 1 whole day! If a kid has a   question, the Robot Teacher is always ready with an answer!   The Robot Teacher can learn you name in less than an hour!               The Robot Teacher has a scedualed time and knows   when to go to lunch or when the children needs to go to their   U.A. When it's time to go to another class, the Robot Teacher   is right on time. The Robot Teacher never forgets what lesson   it was on for each class and never has to be reminded to post   attendence.               The Robot Teacher is a little strict though. It can sence   when a kid is chewing gum. It always knows when a child is   whispering. The Robot Teacher knows when a student is not   listening or being bad. It also knows when to send its student   to the office.       The Robot Teacher is a great teacher for children. It is very   entertaining and has a fun way of teaching children!

Item_Response: It was just a regular spring day for 11 year old Hannah Brown. She had just gotten home from middle school when she heard a strange sound from her bedroom. She thought, oh it must be my guinea pig running on his wheel again. She was far from right. The noise stopped. Hannah wanted to get some markers and colored pencils for her project she was working on for school in her bedroom. What she saw on her bed would change her view on life forever! It was a little robot! It was turned off but Hannah was screaming at the top of her lungs! She wanted to tell her Mom but she was at work, so was her Dad! Hannah was like, 'WHAT THE HECK DO I DO? IT MIGHT KILL ME!' She was so flustered by the idea of a robot of having a in her room, she didn't even notice that it was off! Hannah had to tell someone so she called her best friend, Shannon Bunker to come over.       Shannon was over her house lickity-split! She lived about a half mile down the road. She was as shocked as Hannah was about the robot! They both wondered, how the heck did this robot get in here, and why??? That was a question they could never answer. Finally her parents got home and Hannah told them everything that had happened in the past couple of hours. They were as flabbergasted as Hannah and Shannon were! Hannah showed them the robot in her room. But this time, it wasn't there! Instead it was on the ground, waving at them! This was too much for Hannah. She thought she was going crazy! I know you people in this club would be very shocked if this happened to you! Anyway, the robot was a small fellow, metal and all. He looked very innocent, not a killing machine. Then suddenly, he spoke. He said, ' Hello, my name is Wally. I come from small planet, no people, only robots. I will do no harm. As matter of fact, I'm here to help.' The whole Brown family and Shannon were in complete shock! Hannah stuttered, 'Help with what?'. The robot answered kindly, 'To keep this house clean and to play with everyone, of course!' Hannah finally thought, 'Hey this might be so bad as I thought!' And from then on, the little robot and Hannah became good friends. Also, no one else knows about this robot so you better not tell anyone!

Item_Response: One warm summer day a little girl named Laney was walking down the street with her friends because they just got off of the school bus. All of her friends had left to goo home so she walked the rest of the way home all by herself. She turned around a corner on the street and saw a metal box, it was shiney so she went over to it. when she walked over and tapped it its arms, wheels,and head popped out. Laney was fritened at first but then it started to talk so now she understood that it was nice. Laney just put everything all together she knew it was robot.       She started to be able to uderstand what it was saying, it told her its name. She couldnt understand at first so she asked it to repeat what it had said. The robot spoke again, ' My name is Roxy.' it said it in its robot voice! Roxy told Laney what her personality was lke and what she enjoyed to do in her free time. Roxy said, ' I enjoy riding around really early in the morning when there is not that much people around to see her, she said that she likes visiting the cars at the dealership beacause they could talk to and they were all the best of freinds.' Laney asked Roxy if she could come home with her so she could tell her mom about her, but Roxy didnt really think that that was such a good idea. Laney was a little sad that Roxy didnt want to come home with her, but could understand.       Laney went home and promised that she would come back there right after school tomorrow. Just as yesterday Laney came off the bus and walked with her friends until they all left and then she went to see Roxy again. Roxy was very happy to see Laney because she could not go to the car dealership because they were having an event so there was a lot of people there. Roxy was so happy to see her that she started riding around in cicles with a bid digital smile on her face. Laney felt really good because Roxy was so excited that she was here. Once again Laney asked Roxy if she would come home with her. Before Roxy said anything Laney  said that she would make sure that nobody saw her. Roxy felt really bad now but again she had to say no because it was to big of a risk. Laney was now sad again because she said no to her again.       That night when Laney was laying in her bed reading a book she heard a noise from outside her window. She went over to her window and saw Roxy sitting out there behind a bush. Laney could still see her though. Laney laughed and went outside she ran up to Roxy and gave her a huge hug. She was so happy to see Roxy that she was jumping for joy. Laney told Roxy to come iside and sleep in her room tonight. She said that she would show her to her mom in the morning when she woke up. She was so happy that she could barely sleep through the night. Laney and Roxy are going to be freinds forever at least thats what Laney says!

Item_Response: The Girl Who Found Out Her Friend Was A Robot.                     Once in a time a girl found and be-befriended a girl at school.Her name was, ' Cindy Loads.' She was an average girl in a small town with the name, 'Taper Town.' She went to school at Taper Town Elementary School for 2nd Grade. Her first day of school was today! March 21, 2007. Cindy's teacher was Miss Lizzy she was the nicest teacher of all. She was nervous when she stepped on the school bus 214, but when she stepped on the bus a girl with black flats, a red shirt, and black dress pants said,' sit here, with me, come on, please!' Cindy was kind of relieved she had a girl to sit with but she did not know this girl. Cindy sat down with the brightly colored, dressed girl Cindy asked,' what is your name?' The girl said,' nicoliabot.' Cindy was blown away when she said, ' Nicoliabot' because that was an unusual name for a kid in Taper Town.               The Two girls went to class with each other asking a bunch of questions each. One said,' how old are you' and ' when is your birthday' all day long. Nicoliabot sat next to Cindy and Nicoliabot stared at Cindy and she mumbled to herself. Cindy did not get what she was saying but she did not really care because the teacher was talking, ' Hi I am Miss Lizzy you can call me Miss L if you want to!' The teacher let us have snack time and everyone was like, ' HOORAY' except Nicoliabot she just sat there. Everyone had food and drinks but Nicoliabot rapidly ran out of the classroom, Cindy ran after her and said, ' what is wrong?' Nicoliabot did not say a word, but pouted. Nicoliabot went back to the classroom and the teacher said, ' Where were you two' we said, ' we were in the ladies room' Miss Lizzy said,' You need to sign out next time, okay?' 'Okay' we said.We still had snack time and i said, ' Do you want some water?' Nicoiabot said,' GET IT AWAY FROM ME!' Cindy was left with a surprised face in a bad way.               Cindy ran quickly to lunch and caught up with some other friends of hers and Nicoliabot with her head down sitting at a lunch table where no one sat at. Cindy felt sad that she left Nicoliabot by herself, but she screamed at Cindy and that was not appropriate. Cindy went to the hot lunch line and heard someone calling her ,' Cindy' 'Cindy' it was Nicoliabot Cindy said, ' What do YOU want?' Nicoliabot said, ' I want to apologize to you about screaming at you at snack time.' Cindy walked towards her and said,' apology excepted with a hug. Her hug felt hard and rough. I asked Nicoliabot,' what do you have under your jacket' she said,' my clothes?' 'Why?' 'Oh nothing' said Cindy. Cindy asked Nicoliabot,' do you want to come to my house today after school?' Nicoliabot said, ' I will think about it as long as astrobot my dad says yes.' Cindy asked, ' why do all of your names end with bot?' Nicoliabot said,' time to line up for recess!'                Nicoliabot went home and asked her dad, ' can i go over my friend Cindy's house? Please Dad?!' Her dad was surprised that she made a friend on the first day because she was a..... ' Dad do not say it' said Nicoliabot. Her Dad said,' That is fine stay safe, do not reveal!' 'Okay dad, I won't' Nicoliabot said. After she said bye to her family she quickly went out the door she went to Cindy's house. Cindy was really excited in a way, but she knew something was up. Nicoliabot knocked on the door and said,' I am here' *knock* *knock* Cindy answered after the second knock and said,' Hello how are you?' Nicoliabot said,'great!' She rolled herself in Cindy's house where it was cool and cold. They went in her room and Cindy Spotted she was not stepping on the steps she was actually gliding from the steps. Cindy asked,' Are You a ro......' Nicoliabot said,' Yes but keep it a secret i thought you would know at the first day you met me on the school bus. Remember?' Cindy had nothing to say but in her mind she was like I'm friends with a robot that is really cool! I knew that you were some kind of a robot because you ran away from liquid and when i hugged you, you felt like metal and know we are at my house and all your names ended with bot i should have known this at the start and i just found out that you were a robot? ' Yup that is very true' said nicoliabot. 'We are going to be best robot buddies ever right' said Cindy. Of course I am Cindy.

Item_Response: On Tuesday May 7,2013 I made a orange robot. I name her Katie. Katie had wings to fly me to school, the robot could shrink to hide itself , Katie could duplicate into anything or anyone, and it could talk.       When i made Katie I checked every wire and little bolts just in case she fell apart. When she awoke it felt great because I made my first robot but of course it was 5:00 a.m in the morning and i had school in 2 hours. Then i  thought well I really want to go t o the moon then i look at the robot that is when it hit me the robot can go to the moon but it will need some claws, a storage, and a camera. I attached it on really fast.      After school I went down to my work shop and did a little few touches and the robot was ready to go to the moon but I had a little problem how is a 12 year old girl going to get a 100 pound robot to the moon? I didn't think of a solution so i gave up and went up to my bedroom to watch some TV. On the news it said the space shuttle is launching tomorrow at 5:30 pm. I'm going and i will camp out in line all night.      At 5:30 it was launching time the robot was already to go to the moon. The pictures were beautiful pictures it was like seeing a new world that you never new about. When I was looking at the camera a astronaut was stuck under a rock. I grab the controls and I got the robot to lift up the meteor and saved the astronaut. Then I flew the robot home.       The next day the president came and asked me my name. I was shocked that the president saw what I did for the astronaut then I said it was nothing. The president said it was something amazing. The president said here is a check for 10,000 dollars and I would like to take the robot and put it on display. I was like yeah sure!      So the president took my robot and i never saw that robot again but I still have that check maybe I should make a new robot someday.

Item_Response: The Robot Wreck             Two-thousand years into the future, humans will be all but gone, and robots will dominate the Earth. Here is a story of a small robot, and how she made a huge discovery, even though nobody believed she could.            'Hey!' shouted Amelia Agribot, 'Give that back! It's mine, not yours!'. . . 'Please?' she whispered, to quite for anybody but herself to hear. The popular robots in her neighborhood, Garry Gower, Delia Dante, and Samuel Scout, had just took her arm off, locked it in Garry Gower's cabinet body, and rolled away.              You see, Amelia was a small, defenseless, strawberry-picking agribot. She really wished they hadn't took her arm, not only because it hurt, but because the robotic parts dealer wouldn't be there until next month, and the harvest season  was going to start the next week.            Back at Delia Dante's house, they were all having a good laugh about the way Amelia had reacted. 'Did you see the way she almost shorted herself out with her own tears?' Samuel Scout asked, between laughing fits. 'Hey, do you guys want to have a little fun before we give back her arm?' asked Garry. 'Sure,' said Delia and Samuel. After they went over the plan, Samuel went home, and got an old sack, and came back to Delia's house.            Twenty minutes later they found Amelia  walking down the street alone, with no adults to be seen. They snuck up on her, shoved her into the sack, and stuffed the sack into Garry's cabnit. Garry locked the cabnit, and they rolled up a steep hill. From there Delia took the sack, and rolled down into a steep volcano. She then tied a rope to the top of the sack, grabbed one end, and rolled out. Then Samuel held the rope and begun to bounce it closer and closer to the hot magma. Amelia just huddled in a ball and sobbed, sure that she was facing certain death, when Samuel dropped the rope. The odd thing was that, even though he had dropped the rope and Amelia's arm, Amelia could feel ground, and she wasn't dead.            For an hour she struggled to get out of the sack, and when she finally did, she wished she hadn't. In the volcano, she could see molten chunks of metal that looked an awful lot like robot frames. When Amelia calmed down a little, she noticed that the ground she was standing on was shimmering in a color she had never seen before.  I wish I could leave!  Amelia thought. This place is crazy! As she thought the ground became brighter, and Amelia closed her eyes. When she opened them again, she was back on her street.            Wow! Wait till I tell Mom and Dad! Amelia thought as she rolled her fastest towards her house. After she showed her parents, they told the whole neighborhood, and they all came to Amelia to grant wishes for them, and Garry, Delia, and Samuel never messed with her again.
