Item_Response: I have tried making a working robot my whole life, but I have always failed. But yesterday, was the best success I have ever had. Heres my story.       So yesterday I was trying to build one, again. Nothing had been working. Then again it usually never works. It was the same as always. Putting parts together and nothing ever working. But that day I did end up finishing it. It looked great but it never                       . After that failer I started to give up hope on ever building this thing. I desided to give up on ever building it. I shoved the nonworking robot in my closet and then went downstairs, hoping I would never work on it again.        It has been a month or so since I last touched the robot. After a while I couldn't take it anymore and started analyzing it. I realized there was a piece that was missing and I though I might have hope if I put it in. But once again it didnt work. I put it back in the closet and left.        After dinner I went upstairs to find a huge suprise. When I walked in my room the closet door was open and so was my window. My robot that I thought didn't work actually did! But now it was loose in the city. I had never seen it work before so I couldn't tell how it would act, and thats when I was worried.          Three days later I saw the robot near a bus stop. I what I was hoping it wouldn'tact like was what it was acting like. It was causing so much destruction. It was ripping out signs from the ground, flipping things over, Then ripping them in half. I don't know one person that would dare to get near it. There was noway to stop it. Nothing could stop it. No one could stop it...............I couldn't stop it. I had made a monster not a robot. This was my fault, and there was nothing I could do...but run.

Item_Response: One warm summer evening George the robot was hard at work looking for lost people down in the mines. After searching most of the day he discovered someone who seemed to be lost. George approached him so that he could use the radio to communicate with the search and rescue team. 'Hello can you help me I'm lost!' says the man. 'We will be there as soon as possible.' replied the search and rescue  team. A short while later the rescuers arrived to help him out. Then they took George back to base for the night. That night they forgot to turn George off and his battery was going to die, but before it did he all of sudden started moving. He heard a child yell 'Cool a robot!'                 The child took George back to his house where he hid George from his parents. He heard them call the child John. Johns room was small and was crowded with tons of toys and games. John spent lots of time with George and he began to be very attached to John. One day a month later John's parents found out about George. 'You better take that back where you found it John!' exclaimed his mother. 'But why!' said John. 'Because its not yours.' replied his mother. That night John was very sad. He was so sad that it made George feel sad. George was imaging what it would be like if he was able to move on his own. He could run away with John!                                                                                                                                                                                                                       George wished so hard that the next morning he could move! He could also talk! George woke up John immediately and at first he was scared. John thought he was dreaming. He told John to pack up some stuff so they could set off on their adventure. An hour later they were ready to. They silently slipped out the back door and entered the woods. The sky started getting dark after an eternity of walking. George was scared he didn't know what to do. Then he remembered that he had a flashlight. He took out and they continued walking. The whole time John was saying things like 'All my friends would be so jealous!' or 'It would be cool if you could turn into a car.' After another hour of walking John wanted to go to sleep, so they stopped for the night. That night he wished he could fly. He wished so hard that in the morning he could fly. John was already awake and eating some of the food he had packed. He was speechless when he saw George fly.                   Since he could fly he let John ride on his back, so they could travel faster. After flying most of the day the came out to a small town. George landed softly in the town park. John said 'George you need to stay away from people or they will get suspicious!' The town they were in also had a mine, so they went to see if they had a robot as well. They did infact have a robot. John asked what their name was and they replied that it was named Amilia. John asked a few more questions about robots and then they went back to the park to stay for the night. George wished Amilia could be alive too. He wished so hard that the next day he went to the mine and Amilia talked to him! He was so happy. They all decided to live near the mine and help the search and rescue team. John called his very worried mother and he went home. Years later he came to visit George and Amilia and also met their children. They lived happily in the mines.                                                                                 The End

Item_Response: A girl named Ally had a dad that was a scientist his name was Jason. he was making a robot that would some day help save lives and hace fun when he was told to. Then oneday Ally was watching her dad work on his new robot. When all of a sudden there was a fire! Everyone had to get out. Ally got out in time, but Jason did not. The robot was still in there and he saved Jason and helped put out the fire. Jason was so proud to be the that made him.                      Then the robot became a hero and they made more! Ally was so proud of her dad she helped make them. Over the summer, Ally and Jason got their own robot and named him Max. He helped them all over the house and yard. Max even helped make more robots! He was such a big help!                 After a long time Max got lonely so for his birthday Ally and her dad made a friend for Max to play with. Max and his new friend, Chopper, would play all day, but still do their chores.                 Next, Ally and Jason made a hut for Max and Chopper. They would play all day in that hut. It made Ally and Jason so happy to see them happy.                 For ten years Max and Chopper played Jason began to see that they were slowing down. So, he made a machine to put in them that would make them be young forever.

Item_Response: The War Robot                 It all began twenty years ago. No body knew what was happening and all of a sudden this crazy moment happened.       In the beggining there was a robot that was helping with one of the wars that took place in the hot humid climate. This robot was a tank that helped bomb places that were bad. Strong and Mighty, the war robot would do every kind of job possible. Such as bombing places, bringing medicine to soldiers who were wounded, and helping carry people to medicle centers that were injured. Although it was very small it got the job done.       During one of the robots missions he was working with peolpe that were also bombing places. So the first day when the war started one of the people pushed a button that woke up the robot. As soon as the robot got turned on him and the other men went sraight outside. When they were outside they saw people that were injured so the war robot picked three of the men up and quickly went back to one of the medicle centers and dropped them off.       The next day was all a surprise. When one the men pushed the button to wake the tiny robot up it started acting weird. 'It's alive,' said one of the men. All of a sudden the robot went straight outside and began to do things like never before. It was shooting at random targets and not doing its job. It would not control itself.       Weird things happened like this for the next three weeks. Finally, one of the men got the scientist who built it to come look at it. After about two hours the scientist came out and reported it was out of control and alive.        In the end the war robot got removed from being a bomber and ended up being thrown away and used as a piece of junk.

Item_Response: On a sunny day I was play with a robot called CARL. It was a robot that can do anything you want it to do. It can get you  a drink of water  or cook you food. Then one day when I was up stairs waiting for my eggs to come from my robot. 'BANG,BOOM'. The robot has blew up the stove. The whole house was on fire and I was the only one home. I went down stairs and try to get out but the door won't open. Then I tried to push it down but it would not work. I thought I wasn't going to make it out alive.  Then everything started to turning white. When I was about to pass out I saw a silver thing coming towards me. I couldn't see anything anymore because I passed out.                                       Then when I woke up I found myself in the doctor's office. When i got up I saw the my robot bring breakfast for me. Then the doctor came in with my parents. My parents was asking me if I was ok. I said ' I am fine and what happen when I pass out'.    They told me that the robot saved me. I was shock when the told me that how can a two feet robot save me. They told me that the robot they bought was meant to save me.                                        A month later I was recovered and the doctor said I can go home. When I was waiting for my parents to pick me up I kept thing when I get home I get to play with the robot. Finally when I got home. I was looking for the robot but it was not there and i check the whole house. Then I went downstairs to look for my parents to see if they have it but the said, 'No'.They told me to check again everywhere and I did and still no luck. Then when I realize I have check the bathrooms but all I found was a broken window and a ski mask. Someone has robbed us. I told my parents about it and called the police. They said that people also said that they got robbed. We told them what it was and they said the are trying to catch the robbers.                                        5 months later there is still no respond from the police. My parents didn't want to buy a new on because it cost $2000.00 dollars. Then the phone rung. 'RING','RING'. We rushed to the phone. The police said that the catch the robbers and you have everybody's stuff back. When we got to the police station I got my robot CARL back. I took it home and I played with it and played  with it and played with it in till today.                                           20 years later which makes me 31 year old and I have a kid. I told him about the robot CARL and what did I do with him and now I am give it to you. He was as happy as when I got CARL my robot. I also told him what CARL can do like cook for you and get water for you and he said that hopes he get to do the same thing I did.

Item_Response: The darkness was enveloping him. He was truly nothing anymore. It was over.       It all started when the SAR Program (Science Association for Robots) had thought of sending robots to Mars to set up bio-fields and colonies. They had done the same thing to the moon, and now that robots did almost everything for humans, they thought it would work out wonderfully. I thought so too.     My name is  Jakob Drake, and I still have the same beleifs as the SAR Program, in fact, I was one of their top scientists. But  their last project didn't turn out well at all, and the human race is a WHOLE loot worse off because of it.       The year was 2029, and with Earth's colonies on the moon and expeditions to two nearby solar systems, it seemed as if the human race would find no limits to our power. But it was our confidence that brought us down. SAR had been thinking about sending robots to Mars set up bio-fields that could possibly be used to make colonies there. Finally, we decided to have a conference with all the major leaders of Earth and the moon. So, within a week of making our decision, SAR was hosting the first giant meeting without any robots to witness it in over a decade. (robots now ran almost everything on the Earth and moon) When all the major leaders of Earth and the moon were gathered, (The leaders of the moon used a simple teleportation device.) the meeting commenced. They all spoke in The Ultimate Language, which had been created after World War 4, when the different cultures of Earth had used robots to help them to keep the peace between the Earth's inhabitants. At this time, the Humans and robots had created the RHAFP (Robot/Human Association For Peace) which became a group of robots and humans who worked together and ruled all places where humans lived.       I was representing SAR at this meeting, and I chose to speak first. 'Now, as you all most likely know, SAR has decided that Earth should send robots to create bio-fields on Mars. I fully support this idea and hope that you will all see the logic that SAR has to present this idea. The first reason is that we believe that as we expand our boundaries, we could find other intelligent humaniod life forms. The second is that we might find valuable resources that have disappeared from the Earth. Third, the robots are growing angry that we have not made a move towards trying to find a planet where they might be able to thrive, and they may soon rebel. That is all I have to say.' And i sat down.       'It is a valid point.' Stated Erin Maelnik       'Hmmm, i suppose so, but what if we do find other life on Mars. They might overpower our robots and that would be horrible for us.' Countered Jon Rinao from Europe.       I came back with: 'Then we shall make our best robots ever to send.'        The arguing carried on for almost 7 hours but finally, the group decided that it was a phenomonal idea to send the robots.       SAR got right to work on making them. Only the finest material would suit our purpose, so we used Moonaglite, which was found after digging incredibly deep into the moon's mantle. The robots were made to look like humans, but with the transparent color of Moonaglite, that was impossible to capture. The gears were made of the strongest that could be used for that purpose, and everything was virtually indestructable. The crew of five robots was completed after five years of work, and then were soon ready to be put into the SpaceJet, the fastest, and most durable Space Pioneer Ship ever. It launched on May 17, 2034.     It took the SpaceJet only  3 months to get to Mars, and our connection with the robots hadn't faltered. They were on Mars for three days, setting up the bio-fields. At the end of the third day, our connection faltered. We could no longer see what was in front of the robots' cameras, just gray. After five minutes, our connection reestablished, and by that time the robots were taking off. The SpaceJet charged every minute it wasnt  being used, so it still had some energy stored from before it had taken off and from teh time the robots were on Mars. And the more energy it had stored, the faster it would go.     After six months, the SpaceJet was able to be seen from the moon. Which was surprising to all of the SAR staff, because, even with all the energy stored, it should've taken 10 momths at least.       We contacted the moon's main command office, because they had the control to slow it down and stop the SpaceJet when it was clear to land it there.       I got on the radio first, 'Do you see the SpaceJet?'       'Yes sir,' the voice answered.       'Why aren't you stopping it then?'       'We can't sir.'       'WHY NOT???'       'I don't know, our controls just wont do anything to it, we are going to have to call for a full scale EVAC we need ships up here NOW!'       'They're on their way.'       We could see it through the Laser-Tele, a high class telescope, that the SpaceJet was still hurtling towards the moon.       'Get EVAC ships to the moon NOW people!!!' I screamed.       'Right away sir,' a chorus of voices answered.       Minutes later, the ship was still going 800,000 MPH. But right before it hit the moon, it swerved directions. It was now heading towards Earth.       'What the heck?!?!?!' I said. 'Get everyone off the planet NOW!'       Everyone in the room scattered to send message broadcasts to everyone on Earth, telling them to go to their town's EVAC ship dock. After everyone had gotten out of the building I was still watching the SpaceJet, trying to shut it down by controlling the robots but it was completely unresponsive. Then I saw them. There were tiny pods shooting out of the Jet, and they were carrying creatures that looked human, except their skin was yellow and their eyes were red. Everywhere the pods hit, explosion clouds came billowing up. So much for peaceful first contact, I thought to myself. Then the one pod hit the top of the building, and all of the sudden nothing existed. I didn't exist, my body was no longer there, and nothing was there. Just endless darkness, pulling me in, closer, closer. The darkness was enveloping me. I was truly nothing anymore. It was over.

Item_Response: This is a story about a robot named Carl. Carl was a great friend to everyone in my family, but he loved me most of all. We use to walk to the park play soccer together. He loved to kick the ball around with me, and I loved playing with him too. That was all about to change. You know what, why don't I start from the beginning of the story.            It all started on a hot summer day. I had just woke up from a long nap when I saw an advertisement pop up on the TV for a robot. The robot had blond hair and blue eyes. Just like me! Right from the start I knew I had to get it. After all, it was less work than my dog. Who would say no to that!        'Why would you need that?', asked my mom        'Well... um...', I was not prepared to answer any questions, 'It could do my homework. Wait, no. It could help me with my homework.' I said with a grin, not sure if she bought in, or not.        'No.', replied my mom            It was worth a shot. Now it was time to ask my dad. 'This should go great!', I sarcastically said to myself.            'Hi dad. What are you doing?', I asked        'I was sleeping.', he replied with a groan        'Oh. That's cool!'        'What do you want?'        'Well... you see... there is this robot that can do everything you and I can do a-n-d I was wondering if you could...', I was almost done asking him if he could buy it for me when he cut me off        'S-u-r-e. Can I go back to sleep now?' said my dad, as he begain to snore again            My face turned bright red and my emotions took over my body. I started to jump, hop, and skip over to the phone. I called the company as quickly as I could and ordered the robot. It's a good thing they didn't ask for the price. The robot cost 1 thousand dollars!           The next day I ran to the front door and flung it open. The robot towered over me like a skyscraper. The whole room got dark from the shadow the robot was casting. He was huge! I ran outside and gave him a big bear-hug. Then I walked him inside and introduced him to my family. My dad was in shock from the size of the robot and my mom, well, there was no correct way to describe my mom's reactions. Of corse the first thing my sister said was, 'How much was that thing?' I just ignored it and luckly no one asked about the price again.            That day I began to train him. I taught him table manors, how to play soccer, and how to play video games.            'I'm going to call you Carl.', I said to him, 'Do you like that?'        'Anything you name me I will like.', he said in a robot voice        'Hahaha! Ok, Carl.'            The next day my family went out for lunch, without Carl. When we came back we couldn't find him. My eyes turned into waterfalls when I found the note he had left me before he left. It read:   'I don't think I belong   with this family. I'm   sorry I had to leave   like this. Just remember   I'm in a better place   now.'   Your Friend,                 Carl        After he left I was an emotional mess. My grades were going down and I couldn't play soccer as good as a could when he was there with me.            When I got home my parents sat down with me and told me they were going to try to look for Carl. My face lit up like a light bulb and my hand started to shake as excitement flowed into them. This was the first time I had felt like this sense Carl was standing on my porch.            The next day my parents called everyone they knew to try and find Carl. The same answer was said at the end of every phone call,        'No, I haven't seen your pet robot.'        'No, I'm afraid not.'        'Who is this!? What did you say? Speak louder sunny!', said grandma   There was no hope in finding Carl. Just then I felt the ground rumble. Then another shake. My mind went digging into my brain to try and find were I had felt the shaking before. Then it hit me! It was Carl! I ran outside and around the corner to were the rumbling was coming from. I ran into a couple of cold metal poles that seemed to laugh in my face, literally. I made a couple more turns to find I was at my friends house. I went up to his door a rang the bell. The person who answered the door was not a person at all; it was Carl! Excitement flooded my body as I jumped up into his inviting arms.        'We are never leaving you home again Carl!', I told him            We walked home together, played soccer, and caught up on each others lives. But there was still one thing that was on my mind, why did my friend have Carl?                                                        The End

Item_Response: Robots make life a lot easier for humans. For example the Google car may cause less car wrecks, and people would live for a longer period of time. Some of these robots work in mines and on farms too. Some of these robots save lives. Robots are not just a thing for the future. They help people in a lot of ways, and they can be fun to play with. Robots do more jobs than humans usually do. Some day, that is why we need robots because they can do special things that humans can't do.       The Gemini-Scout does a lot of things for people. This robot has a radio, tells miners when the air is safe, and uses a thermal camera to find living things. The Gemini-Scout is a robot that saves lives. Even though this robot is less than two feet tall, it is a very strong robot. The Gemini-Scout even has wheels. It drags hurt people to safety, and carries food, water, and other important supplies. Thsi robot collects a lot of useful information.       Dante 2 is most likely a robot for scientists because it climbs in volcanoes to find important information for scientists when it is too dangerous or hot for scientists to enter. Dante 2 can do things humans can't do. This robot climbs steep walls of volcanoes and survives the heat of the volcano. This robot can do most of these things because it has eight legs, like a spider. Dante 2 looks for vents, or holes, in the crater. Now that Dante 2 can do all of that, scientists can study volcanoes up close when they are safe in their laboratories.       Mr. Gower is another robot that saves lives. This robot works at hospitals to help doctors and nurses find the right medicine for their patients. Mr. Gower can do anything and go anywhere in the hospital. Mr. Gower is so strong that it can pull five hundred pounds. It can even say, 'Calling elevator' or 'Your delivery is here.' This robot allows them to focus on other important tasks.       Now, I'm going to talk about an agribot. Agribots pick fruit. Farmers will probably use these robots the most. Agribots come in all shapes and sizes. In Japan, there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of the berries. This helps the robot know when each berry is ripe. Now at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, scientists are working to grow cherry tomatoes with no human help at all. They have created a greenhouse full of plants that are cared for by small agribots. Agribots may seem unusual now, but one day they may be common on farms.       Some robots even play with you if you need a friend to play with. Some of these robots are even like pets. They recently made this new robot that has fur just like your dog, cat, rabit, or hamster. You can pet this robot exactly how you pet your real living pets. These robots even play all by themselves. A couple of college students in Oregon created robots that can play hockey or shuffleboard on their own. They know how to play so you don't have to explain to them how to play. They don't need help picking up the puck either. The robots grab the puck, turn, twist and complete to score. Now, these robots have to push the puck to the goal without being told what to do. I think that is really cool.       Now, I'm going to talk about the Google car again. The Google car drives all by itself. You can just sit there with your hands on your lap then the Google car steers without you using your hands. This car can adjust the speed. It tries to match speed with traffic too. Google had to convince the state Legislature to pass a law making robotic cars explicitly legal. These cars have a laptop showing him what the car can see. Google's vehicle is a giant leap forward. Even if it is going seventy miles an hour it smoothly drives along the road. Google's vehicles has driven more than 200,000 miles over highways and city streets in California and Nevada. Google did this testing in kind of a legal limbo. If anything went wrong, Google would have had a huge amount of explaining to do. So last year, the company hired a lobbyist in Nevada. Companies will be able to apply to test self-driving cars on Nevada roads. Google says it will be years before cars like this go on sale. Jurvetson, the venture capitalist, says he's convinced this technolgy could save thousands of lives 'today, already, right now.' Robots are never distracted. They don't text or drink or get tired. They see things no human can. Hawaii, Florida and Oklahoma are already following what Nevada did with these Google cars. One day we may be asking ourselves if humans should still be allowed to drive.

Item_Response: The Robot that Came to Life             It was 1994 in the west of the United States.There was a boy called Octavio and his birthday was coming up.His parents asked him daily,'Octavio have you thought of what you want for your birthday?' and for days his response was, 'No.'. There were only two days left for his birthday and one by one the days passed.         It was the night before his birthday and he could not fall asleep.He was still thinking of what he wanted for his birthday.The minutes that passed seemed eternal until finally he had it.He knew what he wanted!Octavio ran as fast as he ould to his parents' room.He said 'Mom,Dad! I know what I want for my birthday!' Item_Response: The Robot       It was a misty afternoon, very odd for were we lived. The fog was starting to come in through the valley, and the huge mountains were partly hidden from view, giving them a strange look, as if they were haunting somebody. This was such a strange place to have one of the most technologically advanced devices in the world. This robot was a jumble of wires and metal, in the general shape of a human, it looked like something that needed much more work, but my father says it will be finished within a week.       It was October 5, 2038, and the robot was completed. My father was in a board meeting in Anchorage, AK to finalize the designs of the robot and get it into production. He had taken with him only a miniature model of the robot to the meeting, leaving me with the real thing. I decided to sneak into his office and look at the robot, and what a beautiful site it was! The shiny silver metal reflecting the mountain tops out the window, It was a sight to behold. I felt the smooth metal of the robot. My hand pressed down a small button and the robot jolted. I was worried it would wake up but it didn't so I decided to leave so as not to cause any more trouble, but as I was leaving the robot made a kind of powering up noise, and it said, 'Hello, master. I will do everything you tell me to, be loyal to you, and make sure no job is left undone.'I responded and said,'I am not your master, my father is, but he is gone right now', My voice was weak, and my eyes were starting to tear up. The robot said,'No, you were the first one I saw, you are my master.' I tried and tried to convince him that I was not his master, but it was no use, I was the master of this robot, and there was nothing I could do about it.       Trying to explain  this all to my dad when he came back was a nightmare, but once it was over with, having a robot was very cool. He could get me juice and soda, play soccer with me, play music through some speakers on his back, and he could even program himself into our car. I had seen ads for the Google Car on T.V. but with this robot we could do much more with our car. Like the Google Car we could all sleep and have the car drive itself, but with our robot, we could serf the web, play games with him, have him play music for us, all while he has more focus on the road then any other human. It really is amazing.       As the winter went by, we realized our robot could ski. He was a great skier and could teach us many new things, even though we were already at a professional level. My mom and my 17 year old brother just got back from a trip looking at colleges and it looks like he is going to the University of Utah, to study mechanical engineering, just like my dad did. They loved the robot and were very amazed at the extensive level of skills it had. We all were amazed.       Many years went by and we got the robot design patented, and we started having it produced by the new company, I Robot inc.. we started out making thousands, then millions, and into the billions. My brother had gotten a wonderful education and started helping my dad out in the robot business. Despite our immense fortune, we stayed in the same house. Our family loved it here in Alaska, and we couldn't stand the thought of moving. Not even to the bay north of here. Where we were was perfect, and we would stay here for the rest of our lives.       I still loved the days when the fog rolled in, and the mountains were just barely visible. It made happy, and calm. On those days I forget the money, and I think about how lucky I am to live here, in Alaska.

Item_Response: A special robot       Mark and Sam have been working on one robot for their whole life. They are now almost ready to give up on their creation and move on to retirement. The robot they wasted their lives away on is The Star Robot. Mark and Sam have been trying to program this robot to its highest capability of being able to revive someone by going in side the body and jump starting the heart.       Then one day when Mark and Sam were still depressed from the last falire, they found the microscopic robot working in their lab. They jump up in a bust of excitement and huged each other. They rejoice that their life dream has finally been refilled. Mark goes over to check out the robot and says 'We should test this baby.' Sam nodes her head in agreement. So they hop into their hover car and ride over the to the hospital to report the news.       They rush in to the hospital to tell their professor about the working robot. They burst through the door to his office yelling 'Its alive, its alive!' The professor who been supporting them their whole life looks up from pill he is examining. Almost immediately his face lights up with excitement. 'bring it to me now!' he says like boy demanding for candy. They hand over the small creation fit in a plastic bag. 'I already have someone in mind to test this out on. He just died of a heart attack, ' The professor comments. He gets up faster than anyone else his age and runs down the hall.       When Mark, Sam, and the professor reach the sick bay they see the still cold man. 'Come on! We need to get this thing in him fast.' Sam urges. They still the micro robot through the mans mouth and it dispears out of sight. Few minutes past and then the man coughs up some blood sputtering to life. 'What just happened. I feel like I just died,' the man grumbled. 'That because you did,' mark rplied barley keeping voice below a shout.       The robot and the people became famous. The crators became rich and live a happy life while the Star robot started saving lives and lives. Until heart and organ falire is not a worry anymore thanks to the little mirical.

Item_Response: 'Beep beep!' the mysterious robot suddenly came to life! Joey now doubted buying the expensive robot at the new toy store was such a good idea. At first, it seemed like the best thing to ever be made, now, he's not so sure. Clearly, he should have listened to his sister and bought something else. Now, its too late.          It had been the eighteenth of May, two days before Joey Cayper's birthday. Joey and his sister Meg had walked to the new toy store on Calitone Street to check out the new establishment since there was only one other toy store in town called Marty's Toys which was on the other side of town. As they walked down the sidewalk, they could see the bright, freshly coated paint and the flashing lights from 2 blocks away. The closer they got, the more eager Joey became. As some of the toys on display near the window came into view, he started walking faster, desperate to get a look at the new-fangled gadgets. As he walked through the door and the bells rang, a young man in his thirties with a name tag with Alseria written on it came to greet Joey and Meg. He seemed extremely nice, almost too nice. As Joey wondered through the aisles and aisles of new toys, he started to daydream, imagining the fun he could have, plus his birthday was two days away! Out of all the aisles and stacks, there was one that caught his eye, one that mesmerized him.          It was packaged in a plain tan, cardboard box, anyone would have overlooked it,  but not Joey. As the Alseria came and saw him looking at the robot encased in the box, he started to persuade Joey that it was the best and most expensive toy in the shop. Alseria then opened the box and turned on the brand new machine. Its eyes suddenly came to life as his gears whirred and he walked around the shop, doing anything Alseria commanded. It almost seemed like a servant to Joey, as he began to imagine what he could do with it.   He agreed to come back everyday until his birthday to spend time in the toy store. As he walked back home, he couldn't stop thinking about the robot. What if someone buys it? What if someone broke it? Too many 'What if's.' As he arrived back home, he ran up the stairs to his room, filled with an endless amount of toys, he decided to concentrate on homework, which he hadn't started on.          On his birthday, he ran all the way to the toy store with his family, eager to see if the robot was still there.

Item_Response: The Story of a Living Robot       Chapter 1  The Begining                             It all started when Alfred Hieneman, a mechanic, was in his workshop. He had scraps of robots all over the floor, and was trying to come up with an invention to change his life, and take him out of poverty. Mr. Hieneman lived in a small apartment in North Carolina. He had a job in a small car mechanic place. Something in his mind clicked and he had the idea he needed to become a multi millionare.'How could I have been so stupid?!' he exclaimed. Then he began gathering parts for his life saving invention. When he was finished he stepped back to marvel at his creation. What he had built, was a humanlike robot that could do various chores around the house. He thought, if i introduced this to a large technology company, they could mass produce these, giving ME most of the profit. Alfred had a devilish grin on his face. Time to drive to Denver, Colorado where T.E.C.H. Inc.'s H.Q. was. Along the was he saw lots of NOW HIRING signs on the doors of various shops. I really am going to make some money. he thought.           Chapter 2 T.E.C.H. HQ                      Before he arrived at Denver, he asked the cashier if he could tell him were T.E.C.H.'s headquarters were. He soon arrived at T.E.C.H.'s Rectangular headquaters. This is it. He thought. When he arrived at the front desk, he asked to see Jason Farmer, T.E.C.H.'s CEO. At first, the said a strict, 'No.' But when he told them he had an invention, he was soon being escorted to CEO Farmer's office. When he was in his office there was a silence. Then Jason spoke, 'Well, What do ya got?'. ' A robot, one to change the future.' Hieneman replied. Alfred took the robot out of the box, and showed it to him. 'That's some complicated stuff' Farmer said 'I like it.' Farmer's assistants took it away for further maitnence. They said that they would add skin and more complex parts, to make it as humanlike as possible. T.E.C.H. soon became very rich off the invention, and so did Alfred.           Chapter 3 The Robot                        Every robot had to be tested to make sure that its voice worked and that all its joints functioned correctly. Every robot passed the test..... except #1565. 1565 had a mind of its own, literally. 1565 soon came up with a name for it self, Jimmy. Jimmy, soon had knowledge of what humans did daily. They all had different jobs, Weird, why not do all at the same time? he thought soon Jimmy began to blend in with the crowd, because he was more lifelike than the other robots. He got a job at a supermarket and was a cashier. when he accidently bumped in to some one that person swore he heard a metallic CLANG and his knee hurt for days. Jimmy had no home, instead he had two jobs, cashier by day and night guard at the museum by night. Jimmy bought himself nicer clothes, a wallet and  a pair of shoes. he bought those three items at periods of 6 months. Eventually, Jimmy had 7000 dollars in his wallet, since he was a robot, and he didn't need to eat. But, every now and then he had to buy a kind of oil to  make his joints move better.               Chapter 4 The End                         Jimmy began to grow old, moving slower as he did. He got fired from the supermarket and the museum had to drop him, due to not as many customers as they needed to have to pay all their employee's. He found work at Home Depot, as a cashier and gained even more money. Jimmy was soon drivining around in a new Honda Hybrid, that could run on gas and electricity. Jimmy bought a gray wig, that he could use to blend in with the old people. He then lied down in an alley and went to sleep, never to wake up again.

Item_Response: In the future, which is now because of all our technical advances I see us as we are living in as the future. In the future everyone thinks there is going to be robots walking all over the place and machines doing everything for us. I have to agree beacuses there are robots who can do everything for us. Some robots drive, some robots go into burning hot volcanoes, and some even help us find trapped injured people but in this place robots are a little different. Lets buzz up to the year: 2028 living in california.                   Our family hired a robot named jogler to do work for us. He would do the dishes, wash the cars, and do almost anything we need. I belive we should be the one working but my dad says the opposite. Our family of 4 were sitting by our pool, when the robot just comes and makes us smoothies. We dont know how he got the fruit or the cups. I sometimes get more worried than I should. This part of having a robot just doesnt make any sense. I never liked jogler. He had a bad attitude when he talked which wasnt very often. I would walk into my kitchen and see him sitting there, just sitting there. Thats all he would do. I told my dad i was starting to get scared. He just said to me, 'Dont worry sweetie, jogler is just here to help and  not harm!'                   When jogler said ' how can i help you?' I just told him I can do it on my own. Living in such a age of technology, I never really liked technology. It just seemed really advanced. I'm more of a simple kind of person. I talked to my brother about how jogler seemed up to know good. my brother, Ryan, just looked at me like I was crazy! He said 'Steph, you need to stop worrying, he cant do anything to hurt you, trust me...' I didnt like it when my younger brother seemed smarter than me.                    I decided to try to take in some of my dads and ryans advice. It just wasnt doing the job. I decided to go to bed. that day had been bad enough. I definitley wasnt living the california dream. I went to bed and had many dreams about robots and the power that they really have. I woke up panicking and sweating buckets. I ran to my parents room and told them my whole dream. They werent really listening because it was 2:00 in the moring. My mom finally told me to go to bed and luckily I didnt have anymore bad dreams that night. The next week got even worse. My dreams were making me horrified. It was friday night and my dream was outagelousy scary. Robots were walking around my room with guns and bombs. One of the robots was jogler. What I thought was a dream was a nightmare. I woke up, opened my eyes, and saw thousnads of different sized robots all over my room.' AHHHHHH' I had no idea what to do. I kept saying to myself is this real. It felt like a horror movie. Somehow I managed to get to my parents room but they werent in there. I ran to ryans room and he wasnt in there either. There were mini robots clawing my feet and big ones trying to trap me.                 I soon saw many people walking around and all the robots were gone. This whole thing was messing with my mind. I went downstairs and saw my family making me breakfast. There was one other person I've never seen before cooking too. When i asked them what was going on they just said 'making breakfast.' I will never forget the thrilling night I had just expirenced. later I soon figured out, that that person helping in the kitchen was joggler all along. I guess I thought it was the future and I thought jogler was a robot but it was really our maid Mary. Some things were still unclear but I just decided to sit down and tell my family my whole dream.

Item_Response: The Baller                                                                 This robot is not something that helps you collect data for scientist, or even helps you bake you mom's cookies. This robot is your personal trainer that helps you be the best you possible could be at any sport. It has has a yelling voice that tells you to do 20 push-ups or to do a mile under 6:45 or that's another 15 pull-ups. If you don't do it, it will yell at you untill you do them.         The Baller looks like a plasma T.V. mounted on a thin table. Then, there is wheels to turn and to move. There is a camera on the plasma T.V. to help you record your data and improve your skills. Behind the plasma, there is also a pointer to all the sports in the world including Dodge ball. There is also just a training switch for you to just train at whatever.          To order the Baller, just go to your nearest Dick's Sporting Goods. but you better hurry, because they sell quick because they're only $75. So if you want to be better at what your sport, The Baller is the one for you.

Item_Response: there was once a girl named Brianna, who was 12 years old, 13 in a week. she was a very curious girl, and if she was not reading she would be inventing something. one day while inventing, something went terribly wrong.she was working on her new invention,a robot. she just finished it and was so excited,  'now i gonna win for sure' she thought.   'Brianna' her mom called   'coming mom!' was her reply   as she went downstairs she heard a bang and then crash.   'Brianna?!'   Brianna went to her mom.   'Brianna, why don't you go outside and play, not stay cooped up in your room all day?'   'OK mom, first of all I'm almost 13 and i don't play anymore OK? secondly i have a big contest that i have to win and my project is done so can i go now?'   'fine but promise me that after your project you will get some air?'   'fine' said Brianna with her fingers crossed behind her back. she retreated upstairs to her room.her brother was singing very loudly to his stuffed animals.   'shut up Jack! I'm working!'   'up above the world so high...'   'Jack i mean it'   'like a diamond in the sky..'   'UGH' Brianna marched into her room and saw her robot on the bed not on the bench where she left it. she went into her brothers room.   'Jack did you move my robot?'   'what you are!'   Brianna heard rustling in her room. back into her room she went , and the robot was now on the floor. 'huh this is strange' she said to herself. she turned around  and again rustling. once again Brianna turned around and the robot was next to her and staring up at her. 'AGGGGGHHHHHHHHH!'   'OOOOOGGGGGGGGGG!' went the robot.   'oh crud, the robots alive' she said aloud   'oh crud the robots alive' the robot said.   'ABC,123,ABC,123.'   'ABC,123,ABC,123.'   'since when were you a parrot?' asked Brianna.   'since when were you a parrot?' asked the robot.   'OK I'm gonna go outside'   'out... side...' said the robot.   'yes outside wanna come?'   'OK'   so they both went outside and the robot was surprisingly like a dog. but he got too close to the pool and  fell in. Brianna had a titanic moment before the robot sank to the bottom. all was lost for Brianna. she went upstairs to the bathroom,when she came out  wet tire tracks were all over her room and there in the corner was the robot. she couldn't be happier. they went to the contest and she won first place. when they got home Brianna took a nap. when she woke up the robot was gone so she assumed it was a dream, but there were pictures and ribbons with them both on so she knew it wasn't a dream. but one day she walked by a dump and there was the little robot, crushed with tire marks all over him and parts were missing from him. 'it was for the best' Brianna said to herself right before her moms car came around the corner...

Item_Response: Robot is Alive               One day I was in my office thinking of some plans to do. Then I had an idea to make a robot. So, I went to gather my supplies to see what i need for it. Then I got all of the supplies put it on a table and started putting it together. Then when I woke up it was gone.       When I saw that it was gone I said to myself 'It is alive' then I decited to go look for it. When I was looking around I saw some tools that belonged to the robot. Then I saw that there were foot prints on the ground. So when I saw all this I thought he is not here. Then I thought he is at the tool store then I went straight there.               When I got at the tool store I asked the man at the frount counter 'Have you seenv a robot' and then he said 'Yes but it left' then I went to look around the store to see if the robot is around. When is got to the nail section there was a whole shelf gone. Then I got closer and I saw the robot there sitting when he heard a sound he ran off. When he left I looked a little closer and I saw a notebook when I read it it said met me at the office at four aclock. Then I ran to the casher and said sorry about the mess and I went looking for the robot.          When i got to the office the robot was there sitting and then I tried to go near him but his eyes would turn a different color. So I went closer and he got up and pushed me on the ground. Then I went to go turn off his turn off botton but it didn't work.When I told him to stop he stopped. Then I went and turned him off.          I called the garbage man to pick him up and take him away. When I got inside I sat down and I said 'I am very lonely'. So I decited to make a robot again. But this time it should not leave. Then I started making it and then I said 'It is alive'.

Item_Response: The Mysyterious Robot                                                         'shkll'shkll' A Robot came to life. One day I was at school and a robot came to life it looked old and rusty.              I was in my classroom and I heard a mysterious noise so I turned around and there I saw a ROBOT! I can tell that it was pink and purple and that it had a lot of glitter on it. The robot which I named Caroline also had a rainbow sticker but you couldn't really see her color or figures because she looked old and rusty. Since, my classmates were scared they didn't want to go close to Caroline so instead I came close to her. She started saying something but I couldn't understand her so I got a napkin and cleaned her, now she was very nice and clean. Suddenly, everybody came closer and she started to talk, this time everybody could hear what she was saying.              Caroline tried telling my classmates that she was a big help in the past but my classmates did not believe her but I did. She wanted to tell them that she was a robot and that  first she worked in the mines, then on a farm, then in the hospital, and finally exploring volcanoes.Eventhough nobody believed her she still knew that I was a believer and she loved that. Caroline talked about how she loved working but the best job she had ever had was working as a robot nurse and saving lives.               I obviously took Caroline home and showed her to my family they said I could keep her but to not make any disasters with her. My brother asked her so much questions and he was the only one besides me that believed that she did all those jobs in the past. Days and months passed and everybody believed Caroline which was bad because she could get taken away from me which did happen. Some scientist came to my house on April 26, 2013 and asked if he could borrow Caroline I told him yes but to bring her back he said he would but on saturday so me and Cartoline said our goodbyes but it was really a goodbye forever!!! I waited and waited and no sign of Caroline I decided just to forget about her, which was really hard for me. Somedays I was so sad and depressed.          Caroline was the best thing that has ever happen to me I hope she is making her dream come true which is working hard like being a mine, farmer, nurse, and scientist. I will always remember her ALWAYS!!

Item_Response: The Amazing World of Robots                    Robots might seem to be the invention of the future but, they are working on farms and many more work places today. Some work in mine shafts, on farms, hospitals,and even in extreme places like volcanoes or cold mountains.                    One type of robot is the Gemini-Scout. This robot is two feet tall with  wheels and is very strong. It can go down and up stairs and even still work while rolling through water. This robot is still strong enough to drag hurt people to safety. Gemini-Scout is usually used to go into collapsed mine shafts and pull people to safety. This robot also has a built in thermal camera to find hidden miners.                               Dante 2 is a robot that researches and gathers information in volcanoes.This robot is designed like a spider. It is designed to climb up and down volcano walls.Scientists designed this robot to survive very high temperatures. Dante 2 has been a big step for scientists. He climbs around the side of the volcano trying find vents craters.                       Mr.Gower is a robot that helps in the medical field. He helps doctors and nurses save patients lives. Mr. Gower is a robot that is practically a rolling cabinet.Mr. Gower has droors on him filled with Medicien for patients.During surgery he gives the doctors  what they need to proceed on the patient.                        The newest robot so far is the talking car. This car can drive itself and even talk! This car has a cone shaped roof which is designed to pick up commands from its satellites. This car can do anything on the road, including making turns, reducing speed, and even swerve around other cars.

Item_Response: Once I had the biggest question in the world. It was 'what if I can bring a robot to life.' The next day my dad and I went to a scientist. We asked her if a robot can really come to life. 'The robot can be alive if you use your imagination.' I did not understand what he meant by that at first.       The next day,  my dad asked if I want to go to the store to buy a small, live robot. I told him I want to make it become alive myself. My dad looked a bit worried. I felt bad for saying that in a mean voice. Maybe I should've gotten the robot in the store.       Later on, I went to go apologize to my dad at the dinner table. I told him I did want the other robot. So he went to the store to buy me the robot. I stayed home with mom. When my dad got home from the store I quickly got thee robot and ran to my room. I thought to myself, 'what if I can make my other robot come alive, too.       I woke up early to work on the robot. I knew how to make it, but I just didn't have the materials. I looked through my dad's tool box. I found what I needed. So I rushed to my room and got to work. The robot I was repairing had a lot of things that you can put wires in. Somebody must have cut the wires that were attached to the robot.       Finally, I put the wires on to the robot's back and it suddenly came to life. I went quickly to my parent's room and showed them that the robot was alive. They were amazed at what happened.In conclusion, that is how my robot came to life. I didn't know could bring a toy robot to life. Now I know what the scientists meant when she said, 'it can come alive if you use your imagination.' Well, I acually didn't use my imagination.

Item_Response: A few years ago, robots were  finally issued to every living human in the United States. They have been cooking, cleaning, and laboring for us, and many people are against it.            Back in 2023, robots were just becoming available to the public. Then about a year later, richer people started buying them. Now 5 years later (2029) robots started going crazy. Most people call this 'short-circuiting'. Today if you see a robot, you most likely want to blow its head of with an RPG or something.            My name is John Parker. I was in the marines for about 15 years and I am currently teamed up with an army of around 300 people fighting to destroy all robots. We're not a government approved army, just what you can call rebels. We don't use robots in our little platoon, since all of them, and future generations, have and will turn against us.            We are constantly on the move, since the robots have all these crazy gadgets and stuff. There are some rumors going around that robots can hear you from a mile away. Well, not all of these rumors are true, but we don't like to take any chances. A few members of our militia were recently eliminated because they wanted to test a rumor that said that robots were to stupid to know you were sneaking up behind them.            Today we are moving out and attempting to find the heart of the robotic race. We have geared up and are now ready to go on the move. I climbed into a truck with a few of my buds in the back. The driver started the truck and we were off into the open.            Our army of men were wearing a radar-absorbing uniform that also prevents robots from seeing us with thermal vision. We are packed with MRE's and ammunition. Some of us are flying in helicopters, which are also designed like the uniforms we are wearing, and the rest of us are in jeeps and trucks (also designed like the uniforms).            We arrived at the farthest area we could travel to without being detected, and the men hopped out out of their vehicles. Almost instantly robots came out of nowhere and started attacking us and men were dropping like flies. I ran to the nearest jeep and took cover behind it. Only about 10 of the 50 men deployed are still alive.            We started firing back, but it was no use. I was the only one alive.            I rummaged through the back of a helicopter and found a bomb suit. Too bad it takes too long to put on, I thought to myself. I threw it to the side and kept digging.            'Wait', I said to myself, 'If I'm trying to advance to a closer position, why not use the helicopter?' I'm already detected anyways.            I tried to start it up, but it had been shot too many times. It would't start up. A few robots walked up to the helicopter, and the next thing I knew, I was in the medic truck driving to the base.            I was seeing a light, just a small light, and it started getting larger, yet it was not blinding. Then it all ended.                                     THE END

Item_Response: Over the years, many human lives have been saved due to the efficiency of robots. Even more surprising, many people do not acknowledge the importance of what robots contribute to our lives. However, since no robot has ever been able to possess the feelings or reactions that a human has, no robot has ever known the huge importance of their existence in our lives either. No robot has been able to accept the good they have done. None, except for Gemini-Scout.                    Although Gemini-Scout was normally controlled by people, and was never before able to make its own decisions, there once was a time, even if it was only for ten minutes, when it was able to do both. In those ten minutes, and with a split-second decision, a small robot was able to save a life.                    As always, the hero's story began with an average day. The one day that someone made a mistake. Gemini-Scout had been neglected, and the miners it worked with had gone down alone, unable to test the gases in the air, and only carrying the supplies they held. Everyone had been split into groups to begin  working. The day was going so well, they weren't being precautious. The miners entered without checking the gases. No one noticed for a while, since none of them really talked much during working hours. And since they had left Gemini-Scout, no one was prepared for the disaster that followed.                    As soon as the miners had retreated back to the surface, they noticed something was wrong. Someone was gone. They called down into the hole, searching for the reply of a fellow miner. No one replied. 'Hello? Is anyone still in there?' shouted a rugged miner. It didn't seem as if anyone was still inside. But someone was missing. That was the moment they remembered Gemini-Scout.                    The tiny robot was their only hope of finding their lost crew member. But, as soon as they realized the importance of the robot, they couldn't find a remote to control it. The miners powered Gemini-Scout on, and hoped with everything they had that Gemini-Scout was able to find the missing person.                     The moment Gemini-Scout was powered on, something was different about it. The robot shot like a dart into the  ground, like a soldier called to duty. The small little robot had never felt this way before: no one was controlling it, most of the workers weren't in the mines, and  yet it still felt a strange sense of duty to find something. It was different, of course, because it could feel things. Gemini-Scout had never before been able to have emotions or feelings, yet with a miracle, he remembered what to do. Gemini-Scout remembered, and once it knew what to do, that was all that mattered.                       It was dark in those cold, dusty mines. Gemini-Scout noticed nothing, and went plunging on through the labyrinth of tunnels, with only the guidance of the thermal camera Gemini-Scout used to track down the lost miner. It finally came to a wall of dirt, dust, and bricks. Gemini Scout had never needed to dig through a wall before, since it was still learning some things about his job. 'What is this? It's impossible for there to be a wall here. The miner is on the other side. How can I get through?', Gemini-Scout thought. Despite its confusion, Gemini-Scout kept pushing through, for although it had feelings now, telling him to be afraid, it also had courage and programming on his side to help him carry on.                       Finally, with the wall broken down and the air tested, Gemini-Scout found the miner clinging to life at the end of a tunnel. At the end of it all, the tiny robot was able to drag the unconscious miner out of those endless mines, and bring him to safe, clean air. That was the last time Gemini-Scout was able to have emotions, but the good the robot did in the short time it had was enough for its lifetime. That day, Gemini-Scout proved the worth of robots, and how essential they are to everyday life. Never again did those miners leave Gemini-Scout out of the mine.

Item_Response: Agribots Come to Life                                                      by Madison Kelly        Agribots seem like a every day thing people would use, like farmers. They are an everyday robot to most farmers, harvesters, and gardeners. What's the bad thing for this? This is no ordinary day for farmer Jake Jones.       Jake was inside one Tuesday afternoon, letting his Agribot harvest his apples, tomatoes, and tomatoes. He thought this was the perfect way to stay inside and chill; easy life. All he wanted was the money without work.            Jake watched his agribot harvest his crops, while hearing his kids, Nathan and Alyssa , laughing away in the back room. ' DADDY! ' Alyssa shouted. Jake ran down the hall as fast as he could to see what was wrong. He looked in the room to see Alyssa and Nathan playing a board game. ' Whats wrong, Alyssa?' Alyssa answered quickly, 'Nathan is cheating!' 'Nuh uh! '         As that was going on, agribot had started walking to go water the strawberries. Suddenly he fell into a puddle and shorted out. That wasn't the end of agribot. There was more to shorting out. Agribot came alive, not a robot, a human.           Jake settled the argument between Nathan and Alyssa, then walked back to his favorite chair by the window. As he looked out the window he sees a weird looking boy run across torwards the house. Jake ran outside as agribot, now a human, came up to him.       'The name's Shay, Spencer Shay' said agribot. 'Do I know you, Mr. Shay?' said Jake in a weird voice. 'Of course you do! I work in your fields pickin' your berries and such.' said Spencer. Jake stood in complete shock.        Nathan ran up to Jake and said 'Who's this Daddy?'  Jake trembled saying 'Uhm.. Uhm.. This is.. Mr. Shay.. used to be agribot.' Nathan knew he couldn't hold it in so he screamed Alyssa's name and she came a runnin' !          'ALYSSA, ALYSSA, ALYSSA! GUESS WHAT?!?' shouted Nathan.  'What??' said Alyssa as if something bad happened. 'We got a new play mate, agribot came to life!' The kids jumped up and down in excitement. 'Care for some fresh batteries and some television?' Jake said unsure of what he spoken. 'Don't mind if I do.' Spencer walked in sitting down on a black leather couch. Jake got a couple batteries and gave them to Spencer. Jake ran away to go call the news and get them over quick.           'Do you like to work? How much berries can you pick in a day? How do you know when they are ripe?' Alyssa asked Spencer. 'So many questions little one! I love to work, about a thousand a day, and I know with my sensors that tell me. Nathan and Alyssa looked in fascination and then Jake called the news.           The news company showed up and started rolling the camera. ' Julie Jackson here from channel nine news, this just in we have a agribot come to life! Jake Jackson here to tell you what is happening! ' said the news lady. ' Well, he just came up to my door, a little wet, checked my security cameras and he fell in a puddle.'           Spencer ran quickly out the door to jump in a puddle to become normal again, because he knew if people found out, he'd be took away from his beloved farm. Jake ran after Spencer leaving the news crew alone. Spencer jumped in while Jake shouted 'NO! I needed you!'         The news crew left and never put the footage on television. Everything went back to the old way it was. Agribot came to normal. Always outside, taking care of his crops. Nathan and Alyssa playing games and fighting. For Jake, thinking of this weird yet awesome experience that he will probably never have again.

Item_Response: One day a scientist named dr. Jaxon Mannered invented a robot but something went wrong and started to attack the city.          May 15, 1987 profeser Jaxon Mannered wanted to invent a robot that could help the city.If this was a success he would make multiple robots to sell for people to have in their home.          First he had to have a design of the robots base or the outside body of the robot.He made it tall and slim with two strong arms.The robot would move on two large wheels in the back and two small wheels in the front for balence.          Then he got to work on putting it together and it took him two hours but he was only half way done with his project.Then it was brocasted on the news.People said he was a fool and that he was crazy and could not do it.But Jaxon was going to prove him wrong and show them that he could do it.           Then he started to put together the battery for the robots energy.The battery was 32 volts that could last two whole days of use.The battery needed 16 contaners of uranium but Jaxon put 32 because that how many volts were in the battery.Then he plugged it up to the wall to charge and the next day he turned it on.           The eyes lit up green then slowly changed to red.Then the robot stormed through the wall and started terrorizing the city.Everyone scraeming and running for their lives.Then all of the sudden you could hear a tower falling.           Then the army had to come to stop the robot.Bullets were fired constantly but nothing changed.The army had a secret weapon incase of such an emergency.The name is the blundergat.           It shot three acid container and injects into any object.Then exploads shooting acid everywhere.Then he takes the shot it injects and exploads and it shorts out the electrical wires.The town was saved and every one was happy.Everyone but Jaxon he served twenty years in jail.

Item_Response: Robots are very clever machines we have made that help us with everyday life. They can go to any place and withstand anything, the smarter we make them they'll grow smarter than us  (who knows they might take over us). Robots have many abilities and many protections in themselves, A robot called 'Dante 2' can withstand very high temperatures.       Some of the abilities that robots have can go on forever. I'll explain some, a 'Gemini-Scout', it can carry supplies and checks the air for any gases and stuff. It can carry injured/lost people if someones hungry,thirsty,sick..etc. It will have the things to help them.       Mr. Gower, It is a life saving robot that can speak at the same time and has many phrases like 'Here you go' or 'I'll get this for you' and it stashes medicines and vaccines in it's body just in-case of an emergency.       Agribots, these robots are like gardening tools that do all the work. They pick off/up the food from the soil/tree, and they analyze it, they can tell if  it's ripe. Also they keep a huge greenhouse full of small Agribots that care for it. If a plant is dry they will water it.       Their are more robots but they do not work only play and do housework. Some of them do not have specific names just regular given names of what they do like the 'Nanny Bot' (yeah i bet you can guess what they do). I'm just going to name some of them directly, Animal bot, Robbie bot, HRP-4c and some bots can play sports.       Their is one last thing I would like to tell you about,'Google Car' it drives it self with equipment that cost around 8,000 dollars. It can drive 200,000 miles without you getting gas for it once! It drives smoothly on the most roughest roads, they say that this car is rare and maybe never go into stores!  If you go off road it's radar will put you flat down on the road again.         Thank you for reading this and i hoped you enjoyed this essay about robots and have learned a lot about them too.                                                                                          THE END

Item_Response: Once there was a girl named Missy, Missy didnt have any friends and she ws lonely. Her family didnt have alot of money and they were in a tough spot in ther lives. Missy's brother Jake had just passed from cancer and they were devistated. But one day Missy was told to go to the junk yard and find anything she could that they could use for a project she had to do for school. She was told to just take anything she could find like old used paper and pencils and even thingd like glue sticks that she could scoop the left over glue out of. She found a few peices of paper but that was all. But whe she was walking back tob her house she saw a metal leg sticking out of a pile of junk. She went over to it and dug it out. It took her about an hour to get the whole thing out but when she dod she was glad that she had decided to dig it out. It ended up being a robot dog. She took is home and showed it to her parents and said 'mom, is it ok if i keep it and try to get it to work again?' her mother replied 'yes, just as long as it doesnt cost us any money.' 'you also need to make sure that it is ok with your father.' she added. 'Ok' Missy said. so she found her father and asked him if she could keep it and try to get it working again and he said the same thing that her mother said.               So Missy got to work on trying to figure out what the problem was and she found out that there was a couple screws and a battery missing. She decided that she would go back to the junk yard and look for the parts that she needed to get the robot working again. She had no luck at the junk yard but then she decided that she would just take a battery out if somehing else that she had. But then she remembered tht she had to sell all of her toys to help out with earning money so that they could have a propper funeral for her brother. So she though about more ways to get the things she needed and she thought of the perfect idea. She decided that she would just simply ask her parents if they had a battery and some screws. She went into the kitchen to ask her mom and said 'mom, dad, do we have a D battery anywere that we do not need? Her mother said, 'look in the droor next to the refridgerator.' 'Ok thanks' Missy replied. She found the battery that she needed and put it in the robot. Then she went outside to ask her dad about the screws and she said 'dad, do we have any little screws anywere that we dont need?' he said 'ya here' and he pulled them out if his pocket. Then she went back to her room to put them in the robot, but the robot was gone. she looked around the room and found it lieing under her bed. She reached under to get it and it ran out of under her bed into her closet. She then noticed that it was laying in her closet and not moving. So she got it out and saw that the battery had fallen out. This time she was prepared for it to come alive and she put the battery bach into the dog. It came to life!                Now all she had to do was convince her parents to let her keep it. She named it molly and she fell in love with her. Once her parents realize that molly didnt eat or drink or do its buisness, they let Missy keep her. Molly had a great life and she never got in any trouble becuase Missy tought her what was right and what was wrong.

Item_Response: Tyrone was a twelve year old boy who lived on the coast of California.Tyrone had his own robot friend that he could play with since he had no friends.One day he wished on a shooting star that his robot could live and breath just like a human.He new that it was a long shot,but he new that the magic of a shooting star was real.The next day when he woke up he heard sizzles coming from the kitchen and boy did it smell good.He walked in and saw that his robot was living just like him!                Tyrone was so happy he nearly jumped out of his shoes!Tyrone had so many questions to ask.'Hey I need to give you a name...how about Jim' Jim liked the name so the two boys became best friends.'Now that I have a name what should we do next'asked Jim'well my parents left me a fortune before they died so maybe we could go to Hawaii'said Tyrone.So,Tyrone and Jim went to Hawaii to have the time of their lives on a safari in the jungles of Hawaii.'Wow this is cool'said Jim and Tyrone 'I think we should build a fort out of leaves and sticks and stuff 'said Jim 'That would be awesome!!!' said Tyrone.They made the best fort anyone could ever build with two boys it had a lake water pool,a juice bar,and an indoor playground.'I'm so glad that we met Jim'Me too'said Jim.'It's getting late what should we make for dinner'asked Jim'how about tacos'said Tyrone after they ate their tacos they went into their room and fell asleep.           For breakfast they had eggs and french toast with syrup on the side.Something seemed wrong with Jim though.'What's wrong Jim'asked Tyrone.'I don't know Last night I was fine now I'm a wreck,and I don't think I can get up'said Jim.Tyrone was heart broken seeing his friend in need so he cheered him up in any way he new how.Tyrone spun plates on his head he made a clown suit he told jokes,but nothing was working.Tyrone looked at Jim and saw him transforming back into a robot,and said'Jim you're my best friend I won't forget you I promise'.Jim was already transformed back already.Tyrone died of a disease 32 years later and hoped to see Jim again,but Jim was just a robot.You can still see their shack in the jungles of Hawaii with a picture of them engraved in a palm tree.

Item_Response: Once there was a robot named Rick. Rick helped his master Jake. Jake had been paralyzed in a car accident when he was a little kid. Jake always wanted to be a NBA player. Now all Jake wants to do is be a doctor. Rick helps Jake with his homework, baths, and going to bed. Rick is just like the friend he never had.       Jake had very few friends. The only friends Jake had was a girl named Susan. Susan and Jake did everything together. Susan also was Ill. Susan had cancer. although Susan wasn't the prettiest one around, she was beautiful to Jake. She was also the smartest girl in the whole school. She had many awards. Susan always made good grades. Susan and Rick were his only true friends.       The next morning Jake jumped out of bed and rushed down stairs as if there was a million dollars on the living room floor. Jake had decided that Rick was the best thing that had ever happened to him. They played and played all day until their heats were content. one minute they would be playing hide and seek. The next moment they would be playing catch.       The next day was horrible Jake had forgotten to plug Rick in. Rick had past away Sunday morning. Jake was so upset he started to cry. he hugged Jake and said I am so sorry Rick. One of Jake's tears had changed it all. Jake's single tear had brought back the life of Rick. Rick started to jump and down side to side. Jake made sure that he never forgot to plug Rick in every again. Rick and Jake have more to explore than ever.

Item_Response: Back a long time ago, there was a country and they had a royal family that always needed help with the chores around the house. There was a queen named Elizabeth and a princess named Raquelle. The king had died long ago in the royal war between Brittan and them. They had no help what so ever so they asked a scientist name Albert Einstein to come up with something that would help them do some chores around the house and help out with anything necessary. So the scientist was in his lab every single day trying to help the royal family. Then one day, he had come up with something no had ever seen or heard of. He called it the robot, he named this robot Gladiator.             He experimented on this robot and put settings and controls on it. He made it speak, crawl, fit through tight places, run, cook, clean, climb, drive, pick fruit, and finally he made it in human form. He took it to the princess first and she loved it. She thought that it would be wonderful to have something around the house that she could talk to and have something to play with. But when her mother saw it, she thought that it was hideous and wanted nothing to do with it. The princess begged her but her mother still refused. She said that they should just keep hiring people to do the job for them. But when her mother realized that this wouldn't work, she gave Gladiator a chance and so they gave it a couple weeks to see how it would work and react.           The next week, the robot had given them everything they had wished for in a maid. They decided to keep it. It had cooked for them, cleaned, washed the dirty clothes, yard work, and even went to the market to buy the groceries for them. The scientist was happy for them. they had asked to pay him, but he refused. He said that all that mattered was that they were happy.           But then when they came home from a ball one day, Gladiator was missing. They figured that he just went into town or to the market for groceries. But the next day he still was missing. They went to check the town for themselves, but when they went into town they couldn't find him. Then when they came back home, he was sitting on the couch. He had come home from seeing his master Albert. They were happy to see him. So for the rest of their lives and their kids and their kids and so on, Gladiator had been with them. He had helped a bunch.                                                                                THE END
