Item_Response: the unexpected life                   His whole life jacob rountree wanted to be an inventor. make cool stuff, find new things and make lot of money. Yeah, that was the life he wanted. He wanted it now! he began to work on the best invention ever. A robot!                   He got all of the the stuff he needed like all the nuts and bolts, the bits and peices, and his tool belt. then he began to work on his blue print. it showed all the details. the battery pack, the lazer cannon, and who could forget the soda machine!                   When he was done, he began to work. for nine hours straight every day he worked on his robot untill he was done. it looked awsome! He couldnt belive he did it! he finaly made somthing!                   He was exsited about his machine. he wanted to turn it on. But he wanted to show it to people. He gathered all of his freinds and didnt tell him why so it would be a surprise and he would see all of their looks of amazment. when they all got there he said 'Behold! My robot!' he reveald it to all of his freinds the collected gasps added to the excitment. everybody started to chant ' Turn it on! Turn it on!'                   Jacob filled with antisipation and flipped the switch to turn it on and nothing happend. 'awwww.'sighed every body exept Jacob. he was devistated. All that work for just a load of nothing.                    'lets go shoot some hoops.' said one of the crowd members. all of the kids just left without helping or even saying 'bye'. Just great. He left and went to bed with the robots charging plug still in.                     at 6 in the morning a bad thunder storm apered out of no where and light the sky with lightning like the sun in mid-day. then came a lightning bolt biger then a phone pole struck the house with great force. All the lights busted out and over loaded every eletrical thing in the house! Jacob woke up with a starttle. He ran to see if his robots ok and the robot was making breckfast! its alive! He was so excited he almost passed out. The robot said 'good morning, master.'                    'You can talk!' replied Jacob                    'yes, master. would you like breakfast, master? i made your favorite blue berry waffles with bacon, master'                     'how did you kno.... uhh, sure'                      After the robots delisios breckfast, Jacob went to show his freinds his awsome new freind.                        THE END

Item_Response: It was Monday morning and I went to my first period. My teacher,Mr. Bradley, said,  'Today class, I am going to give you an assignment to build a robot.' Everyone was so suprised, because we had never built anything in my first period class before, but we were all super excited. Our assignment was to build a life-sized robot that worked. I was thinking and i just couldn't figure out what to build, so I called my best friend, Claire. Claire said that she was building a robot that did your make-up. I knew Claire was really into doing her haor and make-up, but i wasn't into that. Then, it hit me, I loved sports so much. I wanted to build a robot who played sports with you.          I started out making a blueprint or plan for how the robot wotld be built. I kind of liked the idea of the robot wearing a uniform and maybe tennis shoes, but that wouldn't help me actually build the robot.           The next day, i went to school and asked Mr. Bradley if the robot had to work. He said it didn't. That was a releif, because I probably couldn't make a robot work, but the idea of putting wires and batteries in it made it look more realistic. So, I made the robot and decorated it, and just for fun I attached some wires together and my robot turned on. I was so surprised, but I decided it was going to be a sports robot. I taught it tricks and how to play all my favorite sports.          On the day my robot was due, I brought into my first period class and presented it to my teacher. The whole class was astonished that it worked. I heard 'wow's' and 'awesome's,' from all around the room and I was proud at the work and the time I spent on my robot.

Item_Response: Mr.Biotic                                                                                    Will there ever be a robot that help scientists study more about space? Well there just is a robot that can help scientists study more about space and his name is Mr.Biotic. Mr.Biotic is a robot that goes into space and has a camera and a recorder on it. It can last more than 100 years in space! He has 4 legs to help him balance and has two other legs that are rockets to launch him. Mr.Biotic has a walky talky too. He talks with the scientists while he is outer space, he can say stuff like, 'Nothing yet to see', and other sentences like a person would say if they were outer space.            Mr.Biotic was a project scientists did so it can be easier for them to learn more about space. While they were designing the robot they had to put a lot of fuel tanks into Mr.Biotic. Mr.Biotic is 21 meters tall and 7 meters wide. Mr.Biotic was also made to out stand heat temperatures up to 980 degrees and also has a attachment so when its freezing cold it warms it self to the temperature where it will not freeze.            Mr.Biotic is a wonderful robot for the scientist so they can help them study more about space and the galaxy probably. Scientist were excited when they first launched Mr.Biotic into space. Some thought it would not succeed and other said that it will not fail. When it got launched smoke was everywhere. Scientists were watching the sky until the smoke cleared and saw Mr.Biotic rocket into the atmosphere. Everyone was cheering laughing with joy. They went to Mr.Biotic's point of view camera and it was in space and the sun was bright with planets and the moon. Everyone was happy when the test was a success.

Item_Response: Marvin becomes human.         It started out as a normal day. Marvin, my robot that serves as a butler, woke me up as usual and made me breakfast. It was my favorite day of the week; Saturday. My plans for the day was just to play with Marvin while my parents were at work; little did they know that they would be coming home to something far different than a normal robot.           It all started when we were playing baseball. It was about 11 o' clock when we started playing baseball in my backyard. 'Good throw master.' said Marvin as he caught my baseball. 'Thank you, and same.' I said as I caught it back. I was starting to get good, but sometimes my throws were pretty bad. I guess that's where it all went wrong; my bad throw. I thought it would just be another bad throw, but it wasn't; it changed everything.           There it goes; flying in the air. Marvin seemed like he was ready to catch the ball. It was coming right towards him, it seemed like it was going to hit him. 'It can't hit him, he will always catch it, he's a robot.' my brain told me. 'Watch out Marvin!' I told him. I wanted to make him alert, even though i thought he saw the ball. Everything was happening so slowly but yet so suddenly. 'It's OK sir, I hav-' That's when it hit Marvin. He fell to the floor and he started twitching.          'No Marvin!' I screamed in terror. There was no response from him. I thought he as gone. I wanted to do all that i could to help him so I went to do some research online. I searched how to fix a robot that has been injured. I rapidly clicked on the first thing that popped up. The website told me to attach the dark blue wire to the yellow wire; that's easy enough. I got a screwdriver and rushed over to Marvin. I unscrewed his head and looked at all the different colored wires. I finally found the wires and attached the light blue wire to the yellow one. That's where i made my mistake. I attached the light blue instead of the dark blue. That's why he started to act different.           We had just watched a movie in science class about a robot that turns into a human. It go me thinking 'I wonder if this could happen to anybodies robot.' Marvin had been acting differently right after I attached his wires. He started being funny and not acting so serious. He acted...smoother you could say; even just the way he walked, he flowed better. I decided to write a letter to the maker of Marvin. I got a response almost immediately. 'I know this may be surprising,' it read 'but this is not the first time this has happened, they get their wires switched and they start acting like humans.' 'Wow, well that's it, Marvin is a human now.' I thought to myself. It took me a couple days to get used to the idea of Marvin being human but that's when I realized; I will love Marvin no matter what happens or what he is.                                                                                               THE END

Item_Response: I woke up to to find my robot sitting next to my bed, staring at me with those blank eyes. Sleepily I rubbed my eyes and got out of bed, pushing it aside. I went to the bathroom to take a shower, and when I came out, there it was again, my robot, right in front of the door. 'Weird,' I thought to myself. Maybe I was just hallucinating. I walked downstairs to make some toast, but I couldn't find the bread. Just as I was about to look in the cupboard, an eerie voice sent a chill up my spine.       'It's in the fridge you know.' said the voice. Slowly I turned to look behind me. My robot! It spoke!       'Surprised?' it asked?.       'Yes' I replied. Instead of responding, it turned and drove itself out the door. I followed it out to see nothing but an expensive convertible parked outside. I walked up to it, and as soon as I did, I heard a horrible rumbling noise. In horrer I looked behind me. A huge robot, 100 times the size of my regular robot, was heading toward me. Just as it was about to step on me, I woke up with a start. It was all just a dream!

As I picked myself up to bring my self from town to town massacaring a total of 923956 people for I had counted the dreaded cops came. I had remembered my hate for humans and continued to hate them as I was turning into ashes.

Item_Response: The Robot                      One peaceful day, there was a man who worked at a hospital as pediatric doctor. He said 'This is so frusterating, doing all of this work by myself with no help at all.' That night, as he ate dinner at a sushi resturaunt, he saw a robot machine that was moving and bringing food and dirty dishes to the kitchen. That moment he realized what would make his job so much easier, if he had one of those machines. The issue was that he had no idea how to buy one or make one, so he asked the owner of the sushi resturaunt what that amazing device was called and he said 'It's called Mr. Gower.' The doctor was so facinated by this and said.' Oh my, where could a man like me buy a Mr. Gower?' Luckily for him, they had and extra one in the back, and they said that he can buy it for 5,000$ so he made the bargin. This helped him so much in his office, it brought him the medicine that he needed, carried heavy carts around, and even spoke to the employees and patients. 'This is a wonderful invention!'           But, one day a terrible thing happened. The doctor woke up, said 'What a beautiful day it is!' but he did not know what will come when he reaches his office. He walked in, but strangely there was nobody there, except for Mr. Gower. 'Good evening!' Mr. Gower said in a very suspicious manner. Later, the doctor was leaving the office and had said 'Hmmmm, this has been a strange day, nobody has stopped by for a check-up.' So he left to go home and set up for dinner.           As he was heading home he was thinking about why nobody had showed up at his office, and did not realize that the roads were empty and nobody was driving, or walking on the side-walk, the city was totally and competely empy. The doctor suddenly realized that and he started to freak out and not know what to do in a situation like this, should he look for everyone, or go home and mind his own buisness. He may be the only person on earth, but he didnt know. Once he got home, it was very awkward, and he tried to turn on the T.V. but nothing worked, the power went out. Now, he did not know what to do. He decided to go on a search to look for everybody, but first, he decided to go get some sushi. As he walked in, suprisingly, every employee who worked there was completely fine and was doimg their job. so he left.         Then, as he was driving down the road, he found many google cars. With THE OWNERS TRAPPED INSIDE! He ran out of his car to go save them but his very own Mr. Gower stood in his way and just laughed 'Hahahaha' and said ' You all will now be my power and my fellow robot's.' The doctor could not believe this and his rage powered up to a high and said ' NO!' He took out the most powerful remote in the world that the sushi resturaunt gave him that can control all of the robots in the world. By one click of a button, he could stop them. Slowly, he pressed that button and all of the robots shut down. Everyone got out of their cars and chanted 'DOCTOR HERO!'          From then on, he was known as the hero of the city and everyday, his office was more busy then ever! Truthfully, he thanked the robots, because without them, he would have never been named the hero, and would have never had this adventure.

Item_Response: Robots               Imagine this, you are in a secret tunnel, mining for ores, when suddenly, it all collapses! You look for an escape, find one, and realize that you are injured and can't move, as well as the only opening is too small for a person to fit through! What do you do? Don't worry, the Gemini-Scout will save you! This, along with many other new robots, is a new helpful way to make our lives easier. Scientists have made all kinds of new, amazing robots; a few robots are the Gemini-Scout, the Dante 2, Mr. Gower, Agribots, and the Google car.             The first one is the Gemini-Scout. We would probably not use this in our day-to-day lives, but to those who work underground or in the mines, this is very useful. This is a remote-controlled robot that can save lives. it is less than two feet tall, to fit through small spaces,and has wheels. This robot is very strong and can carry a human to safety. It also carries food, water, and supplies to the emergency.Not only does it save lives, but it helps lives by collecting information to avoid further disasters.              Next is the Daunte-2. This robot climbs volcanoes to gather information for scientists. This robot has eight legs to help it climb the steep volcanoes that it encounters. It also can withstand great heat that a normal person could not. It collects information by studying the gasses that come out of vents from the volcanoes.Thanks to this new invention, scientsts can learn more, and stay safe.              Third is Mr. Gower. He is the one who works in hospitals. He carries medicines that doctors or nurses need. He helps save time that can be used for more important matters. He can go anywhere he needs to as well as talk to patients. Not only this, but he runs on batteries so if he charges for two hours, he will run for twelve hours. He helps make the doctors and nurse's lives easier.              Then there are Agribots. They are robots that can pick fruit. An agribot might pick berries, oranges, grapes or apples. These robots are not used often, but farmers adore them. Since you pick different fruits different ways, there are many different shapes and sizes that agribots come in. Some are manually operated,and some move on their own. Amazingly, there are robots in Japan that can sense when a fruit is ripe! In some schools, they are even trying to grow fruit without any help from humans at all!              Finally, there is the Google car. This car is no ordinary car, it can drive itself!

That night I heard a something break in to my house I went to find out what it was. It was the Susiebot! Item_Response: ZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZ!  'It's ALIVE, it's ALIVE!!!' I screamed.  My 'The Boss 2000' robot invention has finally worked.  Now that I have a new robot I will be able always have a friend wherever I go.  He will be a great athlete, good at board games, video games, and help me do my chores to get my weekly allowance.                                                                                                          I tested my robot out by taking him to the gym to play a pickup game of basketball with some friends of mine.  His only non human-like feature was the nails in his body, but maybe he would be mistaken by my friends as a new kid and they wouldn't think he was a robot.          It was a big mistake making him an unbelievable athlete because he could dunk, but my friends and I were only 11 and couldn't even touch the net.  My friends and I played all of us against him and he still won 21-0.  At the end, I had to tell them he was a robot because otherwise they might think they were terrible at basketball.         The next thing we tried was going home and playing NBA 2k13 on the Xbox.  This was closer than real life basketball, but he still whooped me!  He knew every cheat in the game, and knew every move which I find to be an unfair advantage.         Then, we played a board game called Monopoly, once I taught him how to play I learned that he knew how to manage money so I decided to see if he could manage my real life money, too.  He helped with my chores and taught me how to manage my money.  Soon enough, I had $235!           His coolest trait was his golf skills.  The first time I took him to the golf course we only played 9 holes and he shot a 6 under par 30!   I decided he should play a round of 18 with Justin Vander Klipp, an 18 year old amateur from Djibouti.  Like expected, The Boss 2000 won the match.  He next played Tyler Thibault, an amazing 35 year old golfer from Russia.  Surprisingly, it was a close match, but The Boss 2000 pulled it off.  The toughest match would be against Jin-Hwan Mish, the #1 golfer in the world from Guatemala.  It was only supposed to be a 18 hole match, but after being tied through 18 they went into a playoff which went to a 22nd hole where the Boss 2000 pulled it off with an amazing eagle from 173 yards out.          The Boss 2000 was my best friend ever and it was always fun to have him around.

Item_Response: One sunny saturday morning my robot was making me breakfast like she normally does and suddenly while she was putting pancakes on my plate I wished for my robot to come to life and actually be my friend and thats when everything changed my clothes, my hair my pancakes where now blueberry ironicly blueberry was my favorite and i told my that I had wanted these jeans and this tunic and the mall and my hair was red suddenly and wavy it was almost like sthe robot came to life and was my friend and then I looked over.   My robot suddenly looked like my imaginary friend, my best friend unfortunetly she had blonde hair that had ringlets in it and wore a white and yellow sundress with pretty black glatieter sandals my best friend had come to life well my imaginary one, I just hoped that she was as beautiful in the inside that she was on the outside.  The next day was sunday, the first sunday of summer break and that day was the worst day of my life sinse I had trained my robot to be a robot to pursue me to do stuff but she wasn't queit ready yet so i was thrilled to see what the real life one is like strangely enogh her name was pickles i know it's strange but I was 5 and now i'm eleven and much more mature.  So as I exitedly ran down the stairs to see my a-k-a robot a-k-a best friend thats when the bad bad bad thing happened as I took my first step into the living room I smelled smoking this couldn't be good as my real life robot came out she said in her high pitched voice 'I dare you to water it so it stops the fire' thats when the bad bad bad thing happened andI knew it she was a come alive truth or dare game and she always gave me dares so I got some water from the hose outside and zoomed back in I stopped the fire this once, but sadly enough I knew what I had to do so I sat down in the egzact same chair that I was in yesterday eating breakfast and wished for my robot to be just my robot not pickles. Then everything was back to normal my clothes my hair even my pancakes, also my robot I gave myself a pat on the back and a sigh of relief.  And yes if your wondering I did finish my pancakes.                                                                      THE END

I asked once I had the received the robo-dog 'That's fine sweetheart now we really have to hurry so mommy isn't late.' I sighed 'but mom..' 'abigail no but's now clean up' 'mom if you would just listen..' 'NOW'  This time the robo-dog lunged at her, In the back room the tv blared loudly 'this just in the robo-dog 3000 is incrdibly dangerous as it has a chip which will cause it to kill anything in sight please do not buy theese dangerous inventions, back to you Pat' oops guess they aren't perfect little dogs. 'what there dangerous'? my mom asked quizicaly the dog now a small lump of metal on the ground was short circuiting and lay lifeless and small 'hey don't look at me I didn't know anything' I said 'well we are never entering anything online ever again' she stated simply ' I don't think I can handle another robo-dog incident again'. Item_Response: The robot   It all started one day at a small town named minivill when the   worlds greatest invention was made.       'Mom come here look, look whats on the tv!' said a little boy   named johnny. 'Its an adverstisment for a robot that never needs to eat, sleep or anything and it can act just like us it would be just like having another member in the family!' 'You dont need that' his mom said, 'It cost way too much money and it wont even work its just a fake so that the company gets money' 'Come on mom u say that about everything maybe this ones for real.' johnny complained 'Ill think about it but the only way im gonna  buy you one  is for ur birthday and if its real and lots of people buy it.' she said. 'Ok' he mumbled as he walked upstairs and into his room.       Johnny sat up in his room and couldnt stop thinking that he might   be getting a robot that acts just like him and that maybe it could be like his brother that he never had. 'What am I thinking' he said to himself 'Like shes even going to buy me one if it is real, shes just saying that so I stop badgering her.' He sat up in his room just thinking  for a long time until his mom called him down for dinner.       He stumbled down the stairs slowly and saw he sitting there,   waiting with no dinner. 'Come here I want to talk to you about something.' she said calmly 'I did some research on this robot u wanted and lots of people are buying them and...well your birthday is coming up and I got a discount on it and it only cost 10,000 dollars so I bought it' 'Really? thank you, thank you so much where is it? he yelled exitedly. 'I had to order it online so it wont be here till tommorow morning' she said 'thank you so much I dont need dinner im going to bed early I cant wait!'       He woke up the next morning with his robot standing on his front   doing all his chores like taking out the trash watering the flowers and mowing the lawn. Johnny went outside and saw that almost all of his neighbors had robots cleaning up yards and vacuming inside there houses. 'This is awesome!' he yelled loud enough for his whole neighborhood to hear him. Johnny let the robot finish all the chores before he started to play with him. Johnny played football with him, soccer a ton of games when he realised the robot had no name so he sat down and thought of good names for a robot. He was thinking stew maybe joe then it hit him 'spike!' he thought 'ya that would be a great name for a robot' And it was settled.       He went back inside adn looked at the tv. The robots were   taking peoples jobs so people never had to work but they still got payed, the robots were taking police mens jobs because they can run faster and they could keep searching for people without ever getting tired.       These robots were making lifes ten times better and years came   by faster then ever and Johnny started to realise how old he was and how quick and easy and fun his life came by. And one day he was laying in bed and he fell asleep and never woke up.

Item_Response: Once upon a time there was a robot named Dave, Dave was a robot that worked in a office for a man named Jerry Colby.                   And one very boring but peaceful morning Jerry went to go have his lunch break and he made Dave come to by controlling Dave's controller. but as Dave came tumbling after Jerry he bumped into Jerry coffee, when Dave fell to the ground the coffee came with him and it splattered all over the robot.              Dave started to malfunction so he started to beep very loudly and was frantically spinning in circles until he finally broke down. Jerry was so mad at himself for not controlling Dave very well because he had worked on Dave for such a long time.            So he tossed Dave into the trash can and went home for the evening. A couple hours later after Jerry left Dave started to sputter and smoke until BAM in a giant mushroom cloud   of smoke coming from the trash can Dave came crawling out of  the trash can and on to the floor. Dave rolled to the door but he stopped ' something weird is going on here' Thought Dave. ' Wait just a minute I can think' thought Dave ' I can talk Dave announced . 'I can sing LAAAAAAAAAAAAA' Sung  Dave.            So Dave rolled as fast as his little wheels could take him. Dave had a really big adventure rolling down to Jerry's house he he saw a semi-truck, he saw an airplane and he ran over a squirrel (on accident of course). When Dave ffinally got to Jerry house he rung the door bell and waited a couple seconds, then he got lifted away by a harpie eagle. As the harpie eagle lifted him up into the sky Dave punched the eagle in the face, so the harpi eagle wailed in pain and dropped Dave in the ground.               Dave wheeled up to Jerry's front door step and rung the door bell. When Jerry opened the door and said 'hello' Dave screamed ' DOWN HERE'!!!! Jerry looked down and got so full of excitement he fainted. As soon as Jerry woke up Dave said' man you where asleep for hours' and just before Jerry could lose consciousness Dave slapped Jerry in the face and gave Jerry a rug burn on his leg with Dave's wheels and then they both hugged and the became best friends forever.

Item_Response: One stormy Monday morning, at West Palms Conservatory elementary school, sixth graders where assigned a project a few weeks ago. That assignment was to build a robot. They where given materials and they knew how to build a robot with different personality's, and effects. But one boy, Jimmy, didn't do anything all week and it was due that morning. In a rush, Jimmy ran to his room and gathered all the materials given. He had twenty-five minuets until he had to leave for school. There's no way I can finish this, Jimmy thought to himself as he looked at the clock. He lied all the materials out on the floor, not only was this a bad situation, but he forgot how to build the robot. After five minuets of thinking things over he grabbed his childhood stuffed toy, he used to be in love with as a child, and tried to trick his teacher into thinking he made it. The stuffed toy's name was Tod, Jimmy got him when he was one and had him since. Jimmy loved Tod, allot! The only reason why he chose this stuffed toy, however, was not because it was his favorite, Tod was a hard stuffed animal, that had a voice box, and could walk.Jimmy was willing to put his favorite stuffed animal in harms way, to get a decent grade. He put Tod in his backpack and ran to his moms mini-van and buckled. In the car, on the way to his school, it was still dark out when his mom said, 'Look Jimmy, a shooting star make a wish!!' Jimmy closed his eyes and wished so hard that Tod could somehow come to life, or at least his teacher would believe he made it. That morning, something magical happened. When it was Jimmy's turn to present his robot, Tod, the stuffed toy, CAME TO LIFE! As soon as Jimmy took Tod out, Tod complained, 'OUCH! Be careful man,' Jimmy froze, he didn't know what to do, his class started laughing and he heard some kids say 'Whoa, that's so cool!' While Jimmy stood there frozen, his teacher said, 'Jimmy show us what he can do!' Jimmy looked around, as other people where whispering. He looked at Tod, and Tod winked. Jimmy looked up at the classroom and smiled. 'Well guys, this is Tod,' Jimmy began to speak, 'He climbes, helps with homework, cleans your room, and can talk!' As Jimmy spoke Tod started doing the actions, he climbed the desk, pretended to do math, picked up a tissue off the floor, and finally he said, 'Hello.' The whole class was in Ahhh, and Jimmy got a A+ on his robot. Jimmy and Tod lived happily ever after!

Item_Response: Have you ever wondered of how an ordinary robot could actually come to life? Being bored having nothing to do and you want to just fool around with something, say like a robot. What would you do if some sort of robotic metal was roaming around without a care in the world.        Summer in the desert nothing to do nothing really on my mind. Minding my own business watching the television I see a program saying, 'Get your robot for only a dollar twenty, it will come to life if you follow these directions that they provide for you in the box, call 1(800)-365-Robot, the ten callers will get a second robot so you better call I garrentee they will bring the box to you in the next 10 minutes!' My mind felt like I was in a bubble that I just couldn't escape. I think in my mind 'Really who would be so dumb to buy a robot and think if they follow the directions it will automatically come to life sure that will  happen.' I just dialed the number because I was bored might as well do something.        So I'm waiting for this robot which is suppose to come to life. They said it would take ten minutes, well I took a good ten minute nap. Then I hear a ding I open the door and scream 'Y'all people said it would take ten minutes, you are one minute late, what do you have to say for yourself  Mr.!' He glares at me for a second. gives me two boxes, I gave him the money, and he ran to his car so fast I thought he was a lion trying to chase a zebra. I took out all of the utensil and used my science brain to know that this piece will fit in that one. I'm not going to lie it was a quick process but how was I suppose to believe that it will come to life if I just press a red button.

Item_Response: Cosmo searched the crowd for Izzy, her precious beatiful robot was no where to be seen . At first she wasnt surprised because Izzy could into anything and could blend really well but Cosmo always new the one thing that could find her. Izzy being just a robot , knewall too better not to stray far from cosmo because Izzy had developed a mind of her own ever since cosmo had updated her system to be more human like . But Izzy was much more than robot and Cosmo knew it too, there had always been this way about Izzy that cosmo feared could make her turn to life which would be a break through but that could happen at anytime but if it happened at any moment then there was also a chance that it could kill izzy.             In case your wondering exactly where Izzy and Cosmo are they are at their own house, yeah I know thats hard to believe that they cant find each other in their own homes but its a big house and at the moment there are 68 people in it.Anyways Cosmo was super desperate to find her, this morning Izzy was an iPhone cover and a fuzzy one to it was making her coffee and giving her a massage and producing 300 bucks all while organizing her closet. Cosmo had had some help five years ago in 2034 and ever since they had the closest bond that no one ever even tried breaking it. Cosmo spotted it, there was a furry tail sticking out of the laundry room and Cosmo tugged at it and Izzy had been a slinky dog the whole time , how foolish of her. Elle looked for her robot for days! but one night her and her mom were watching the news and there was a report of a strangelittle robot wandering around town! The news casters said she was 2 feet tall had a silver body and a pink hat on! At that moment Ele realised that Izzy had come to life! So right away Elle rushed outside and ran down town!               Righr when she got there she saw Izzy in the sky! She was givving people lifts just like a taxi would but in the air! Elle waved her arm as high as she ever had and called 'IZZY IZZY ITS ME ELLE DOEN HERE!' Right waay Izzy flew down right away and and kinda checked Elle out. Then Izzy gave Elle a huge hug! But she finnaly just believed it and just had to take some time to get use to her.                            Elle was so happy that her Best friend had come to life! All the children ran inside the house and hid underneath Volkner's bed. When it was safe to come out, all the children asked the same question, 'Why is your mother so mad?' Volkner could not answer.                                         ***   'What is 872+546 Volkner?' The teacher asked. ' Uh, 1418?' 'Correct.' Rinnnnnnnnnng. 'Well class time for sience. Item_Response: There once was a robot that came to life, He was the Bob-123. He could do  household chores and do your homework you name it! But there was a time when it was raining out and a miracle happened to the Bob-123 that would change what he does a lot. It all started with 2 little boys dreaming of  having a robot. 'Man tristen, imagine what we could have a robot do!'' Said Burndy as usual.             'We really need to figure out how to make one' Said tristen 'Its harder then it looks' Burndy replied. That night tristen had the idea of actually trying to figure out on how to make one. 'It cant be that hard' Tristen thought to himself 'I mean its just a couple gears and wires isn't it?' Hours of studying tristen had gotten a idea. He stayed up for hours making a robot in his garage until he had made it. The next day he went to burndys house. Burndy was in his backyard until tristan came along. He told him to come over to his house to see something.         'What for?' Burndy said 'Something amazing' said tristen urgent to get burndy to see what hes made. 'You never take me to your house this better be important!' Said burndy frustrated. When tristen managed to convince burndy to come inside, Tristen asked him something. 'You promise not to tell anyone or show anyone?' 'Why?' Said burndy 'Its something I want to keep a secret.' 'Fine I promise' said burndy rolling his eyes, Tristen then opened the door. 'Its a giant tarp' burndy said With sarcasm, 'Whats under the tarp though' tristen smiled. Tristen then ripped the tarp over the robot shaped object.       Burndys Mouth went wide, 'Is it actually a working robot or is it just another robot cut out?' 'Its a really working robot' said tristen. 'HOW?' Burndy yelled in excitement 'I looked it up yesterday.' 'Wait so for all these years weve been sitting there wondering how to make a robot when we could have just looked it up?' Said burndy frowning 'Pretty much yeah' tristen replied. 'It was pretty hard though' said tristen 'I DONT CARE i just want to see what it does' Burndy said jumping up and down in excitement. 'It can do anything you tell it to do' Said tristen, He then had flipped the switch and the robot sparked to life. It had glowing yellow eyes and very long arms with three claws on each arm. It drove around the room, 'Go pick up that' Tristen said to the robot as he started heading over there right away. 'What should we name it?' Burndy asked, 'Bob-123' said tristen. 'Sure why not' said burndy 'Man this is going to be a sweet summer, We have our very own robot!' Said burndy again.           One month later they were used to there robot getting them drinks and doing there homework. Sometimes they would get in fights on who the robot would take care of each week. But after about a year something happened, It was a dark and stormy night when something happened that is still mind blowing today. The robot was doing chores as usual when something happened.They had forgot to program him to realize the forecast. Tristen Had thought hed just tell him to stop before he went outside. It worked for all that time, but Tristen was asleep This day and when the robot went outside...   BAM! There was a loud shock noise and a miracle had happened. Instead of actually burning out the robot had somehow came alive to become a human. Tristen did not know this happened so the next morning he woke up to find a kid about his age lying on the porch. He was unconscious when he took him to the hospital.       When they got to the hospital The doctor took him in and he was out within a day. 'Who are you?' Tristen asked. 'Im Bob-123' Bob said as he smiled 'Wait WHAT?' Later on he took him to burndys house. 'Oh hey tristen' Burndy said 'Who's your buddy?'   'This is Bob-123' Tristen said. Burndy in disbelief Said 'But Bob-123 is a robot.... Not a... a HUMAN!' 'Bob came to life last night' Tristen had bob explain all of what happened. Years later they stay best friends even though bob doesn't take care of them anymore. That's the story of how Bob-123 had turned into Bob the human.

Item_Response: The Wiggly Robot       One the first day of November I was a little frightened or a lot more than a little, my robot scared me to death. It was supposed to be a fake non-moveable robot but on this day he moved his arm. It's fragile little metal arm had moved!       But even though I had seen this unbelievable thing it still didn't stop my curiosity, I still wondered if this robot that I had just bought from the toy store was alive. So I turned around to see if it'll move while I wasn't looking and it did. It was sitting on my bed before but then it moved to the floor. I said to it 'I know your alive just say something!' But he didn't move he just sat there. So I said it again and he moved, he also said something too. He said 'I am Bloop, what is your name.' Then I told him that my name was Richard.       This robot was helpful for a lot of things like doing my chores, doing my homework and doing anything I wanted him to do. He was a loving and caring robot, but it turned out that this robot had been accidentally been put in the toy store it was actually a robot being tested to see if it would sell. I would say that this is the best robot ever.       But since this robot was used for something else I took it back to the toy store to make sure it went back to the right place. When I got there the man who owned the robot was there he was happy to see the robot. I told him that the robot was the best thing that I had ever used, then he said I could keep it for helping him test it out. I was so happy to know that my fun was helpful and to know that I got to keep the robot.

Item_Response: I've always wanted to build some sort of mechanical device.  I thought what if I make the most famous robot to be ever created?  That would be pretty cool.  I started to think about what my robot might do.  So, I began to plan on paper.      I stayed up for hours trying to figure out how to build this thing.  I stayed up so late one night that I slept in until later than noon.  But I guess I can say that it was all worth it.  Because after a week, which in my eyes felt like a century, I came up with the perfect idea.      'Mom!' I shouted from down the hallway.      'Yes, Brandon?' she replied back.     'I was wondering if I could, you know, build some sort of a robot?'     'Oh course I will,' she says.  'You, your dad, and I could get started on it now.'     You see, my parents are scientist, and are really good at making mechanics and all things in that nature.  They even own their own laboratory, that I sometimes would stay in and mess around with the gadgets.      'Thanks Mom.' I said, smiling.     After explaining to my dad about the robot concept and all, we headed to the laboratory to work on the robot parts.  We started collecting all the necessities for building a robot.  After about thirty minutes of collecting the necessary things, we got straight to work.  We looked at the blueprints that I made, and my dad got started on the base.  My mom and I started on the micro-chips and all the electronics that we would be using for the robot.      'Done with the base,' he says, wiping sweat from his forehead.     'Wow Dad,' I said in awe.  'It's awesome!'     It was a really simple task to get the electronics, but putting them together was going to be a nightmare.  We decided to get right on with putting the chips and other electronics in the base, so we could try and get the more difficult part out of the way.  I started to sweat because I felt so concentrated on getting the hard part out of my way.  It was around dinner time, so we took a break.  We called a local pizzeria, and got two large pepperoni and mushroom pizzas to go.      I was so hungry, my mouth started to drool at the sight of pizza and pop.  I scarfed it all down as quickly as I could, chugging my pop.  And let me tell you, that was some good pizza.  My mom told me to slow down because I'll choke.  Did I listen to her?  No.     After resting for an hour, we got back to work.  While my mom and I were trying to get the chips in place in the robot's base, my dad started on the neck, head, arms, and legs.     Once I put the last micro-chip in carefully, I shouted at the top of my lungs, 'Hallelujah we're done with the hard part!'     My mom patted me on the back and my dad couldn't help but laugh at me.  Since my dad was working on the neck and legs, my mom decided to work on the arms.  I took another sip from my cool drink, and started working on the head.  I felt my eyes drooping downwards.  I knew I was going to fall asleep soon.  But I couldn't, I wasn't going to let sleep over power me... never!  But, eventually, it did.  I smacked my head on the table but didn't care... I was too tired to anyways.     My dream was spectacular.  The robot was a success, and I made millions and millions of dollars on the robot selling out of stores.  It was the good life in my dream.  'Brandon!' my mom shouted in my ear.     'Brandon, wake up!  We finish the robot for you... want to come and see it?' she added.     Remind me when I'm rich and famous to give the credit as well to my parents for helping me.     And it was the best looking robot I've ever seen.  It was shinning silver, and it looked like its been polished.  It was quite small, but a good size to be around the house.  It looked great.  'Wow, thanks Mom... thanks Dad!' I said loudly, smiling.     'Go ahead and try it.' they said.     I went out to touch it.  It felt cold, so I turned the switch in the back on.  It started making all these weird noises.  Maybe it was a pro-to-type and needed to be fixed.  The glass blue eyes that they once were turned to a bright shade of glowing red.  Then the little robot shouted in its robot voice, 'Destroy human kind!'     Well that's not a good sign.     'Mom, Dad!  We got to destroy the robot before it destroys us!' I yelled, running away form the evil robot.     'Don't you think that we were thinking the same thing?!' my dad yelled back.     Somehow, the robot got bigger and bigger, until it was the size of my dad.  So that's one big robot.  It started charging at me, and I started to run out the laboratory.  It followed me, breaking down the giant metal doors and the hinges.  I kept on running, and headed into town, not thinking at all.     It wasn't the best idea to bring it into the town.  I just but lives at danger.  So I have to destroy the robot myself.  I grabbed the sharpest thing that was close to me: a pen.  Oh well.  I jumped onto the robot, it fuming in anger.  I heard civilians scream in terror, to help me.  But I was completely fine.      'Destroy human kind!' it shouted again, but louder.     I tried to find the switch button, but I couldn't find it.  That's when he flung me off his back, and I hit the ground with a thud.  That one hurt.  The robot ran over to me, pointing his fists at me.  They turned into blasters.  I quickly turned out of the way, making the robot miss.  I ran as fast as I could behind the robot, and found the switch button at last.  I turned it off, and the robot fell dead.      Everyone cheered, and my parents caught up to me.  They asked me if I was alright and if I was hurt.  Honestly, my back still kind of hurts from when I fell, but other than that I am fine.  We hulled the robot body over to the laboratory, and destroyed it like I promised myself.  We do have to get a new door, since it got busted open.  And the street road that the robot blasted has to get re-paved.  But other than those things, everything is alright.  Thank goodness that no one was seriously hurt.     Now I know not to try and make robots again, because I do not want that to happen again.  So instead of science interests, I found a new interest: creative writing.  It took some years to figure out that I am in love with writing.     And who knows... maybe I'll right a short story about my robot incident.

Item_Response: This is a story about how my friend and I built a robot named George. George the robot helped my friend and I win the science fair and the $50 prize that goes along with it. Goerge was tricky to make but it was all worth it in the end. Here is my story of George the robot...                I was sitting in my living room watching my favorite show, Spongebob Squarepants, when my friend Shannon calls. Shannon asked if I wanted to be her partner for the national science fair. I said,'Hold on I need to ask my parents.'after a few minuetsof explaining about what the national science fair was, they finally agreed to let me be Shannon's partner. When I told Shannon, she said,'Sweet come on over. I think the science project should be a  remote control robot.' Then I said,' Cool idea I'll be right over.               While we were working on the robot Shannon told me how to put together a robot because she went to a cmp called CAMP ROBOT. So I let her tell me what to do since I had absoluteley no clue what I was doing. she told me,'Connect the red wire to the green wire.' Then I said,'What green wire? There are four of them!' Then we both started giggling like crazy then she said,'OK, now that you have put the wire into the green wire, we need to put data in it like what is the robot going to say at the science fair to impress the judges? How about I love the science fair?' 'Great idea!' I said, 'How about we name the robot George instead of calling it 'the robot'?' 'Cool, I like the name George!' Shannon said. Then she said, 'OK, now that we have George all done, lets see how he works. Go turn on the remote control.'                After I turned on the remote control, the robot's, I mean George's, lights started blinking and he started to say,'I love the science fair.' Shannon and I were so happy that we gave each other a big hug. The next day Shannon's mom drove us to the science fair and helped us set up George in a position that he looked like he just won a nobel prize for bravest robot. 'I hope nothing goes wrong with George before the judges show up.' Shannon said nervously. Then I said,' Nothing will go wrong. I promise.' It turns out I was right nothing did go wrong. In fact, everything went perfectly! The judges showed up George said his line his lights flashed in a cool patern and we won first place! Shannon and I split up the prize money of $100 evenly between us. 'I told you everything would be fine!'I siad at last. Then she said I never doubted you. Not for a second.           So, as you can see, George the robot helped Shannon and I win the national science fair and the $100 prize that goes along with it. I used my half of the money for a summer opening to CAMP ROBOT so I can learn how to make amazing robots like george. During CAMP ROBOT I made a robot  and named it BOB. Now Bob helps me with my chores around the house. Oh, and if you wanted to know where George is, he is on display at city hall so everyone can see how George won and why he was worthy of winning a science fair. He also got a medal. Not for being the bravest robot, but for being the most advanced robot made by kids.

Item_Response: Salutations my friends. My name is Koi (like the fish) and I live in Clearwater, Florida on coast and this is my story on how helped the animals in the ocean be saved from  polluting people. I hope that my legacy will live on and that we will be more aware of the things that were doing to Mother Nature.        when I was little in my years of 2220, I had an obsession of sea animals. My hope is that because of all the new high technology, there were many polluting substances that can ruin most of the sea.I came up with a prototype of a robot that can save all marine dwellers and help them if they're in need of assistance.I went to bed that night in hope of my dreams coming true and little did I know that that would happen.          When I woke up the next morning,after the big thunder storm,I saw my robot sitting there and a light switched on.Now this was only a prototype, but with the high voltage system I used, the lightning storm probably switched it on. Yes,I made it so that it was voice commanded and but it isn't built to do all that stuff like dancing, signing, homework and what-not.My robot has a slim, body with many little ,long silicon arms that help the Animals during operations and to help feed them.It is (obviously) water proof and able to carry 450 lbs. and swim with it's submarine-like tail. I took it down to my work and down there I was working with some of my marine animals that I happened to catch before it was to late for them. My robot I guess had a way that soothed the animals during their operations. My robot even does the operations for me. My robot is a very big and tremendous help to my studies and work.After the help, I decided to name the marvelous accident of a robot.           I soon figured out a name for the Robot and I called it MADOS, (Marine Animal Distress Organizer and Soother).I patented  my idea and I sent it in with the blue prints and the high voltage system that I used that one night. A couple of weeks later, I figured out that they approved my Idea and that they would set up an organization to help protect marine life and the oceans as a bonus. I  soon found that MADOS was being used all over the world by Marine veterinarians   and in soothing animals in distress.            I hope now that I've summed up my story that you will keep it going and that because this might seem fake to you , it isn't. I hope that from this story you now understand the importance of MADOS, my best invention.

Item_Response: Bobby 1 wasn't an unusual robot. He was a butler for the Mills family, played with their five kittens in his free time, and often just sat awaiting his masters' orders. This was the exact opposite for Joey 8 who was programmed to cause havoc and confusion. Yes, Bobby 1 was an average butler robot of the year 2052. He was until..........       It was a cold blustery day in October and Bobby 1 was outside tending to the garden when a thunderstorm rolled in. Bobby 1 didn't care, he was robot after all, and water proof at that. Anyways, he kept working under his masters' orders. He kept on working, not noticing the havoc the storm was wrecking. It would later be called Hurricane Zacharia though it was only a grade one hurricane. He kept working on and on not noticing the house. Not hearing the people screaming. They hadn't given him orders, and he only followed orders, so he didn't respond to the clamor. Lightning flashed and thunder rolled. It was a scene from a nightmare! Rain came down in torrents and lightning struck everything made of metal, including Bobby 1. The pain from it sent a jolt through his body. He then thought, 'Wait a minute! I'm a robot! I can't feel anything! Then again I'm a robot and I can't think, SO WHY AM I THINKING!' Things were going hazy and he closed his eyes, thankful of the mercy of unconsciousness.       He woke in a daze. Joints stiff and head throbbing, he looked around. 'Wh-where am I', he stammered,'Wait, I can talk?' and then he recalled the storm. He looked around. 'This isn't where my masters live', he thought, 'How long have I been unconscious? Why can I think? How did I get here?' He had so many questions he thought his circuits were about to burst. He finally noticed the other robot in the room. 'The sleepy head has finally woken up!' it boomed. 'Where am I?', Bobby 1 demanded. The other robot just laughed,' You don't know yet? You're in Thor's palace!' Bobby 1 fainted.       Once he woke again another torrent of questions boggled his mind,'Why am I in Thor's palace? Who is the robot that greeted me earlier?' ,and again, 'WHY CAN I THINK AND MAKE MY OWN DECISIONS?' He tried to get up but nearly collapsed from the pain. 'So this is what it feels like to be alive he thought. Wait I'm alive? I'M A LIVING ROBOT! IT'S A MIRACLE!' Soon he heard a stream of complaints from the nearby rooms, 'We all are! Stop your blabbing! I'm trying to fall asleep!' and so on. Their words stung him like a mob of hornets.'Some friends you are', he muttered. Later in the morning, a maid came in and delivered some food to him.'Eat it up', she said, 'You haven't eaten in days!' When he felt he could stand, Bobby 1 went out to explore the palace. Right outside his door, however, was a guide robot. He wondered how long the guide had been standing there. 'Good afternoon sir. My name is Nick 3 and I will be your guide.'       They toured the castle and Bobby 1 got to see Thor. While seeing him, he asked, 'Why am I alive?' ,and, 'Why me and not my friend, Joey 8?' All Thor said was, 'You are alive because you are a strong and friendly robot. I will let you in on a secret though. If you can find peace here, you will know why I chose you and not your friend.'       Over the next few weeks, Bobby 1 tried to find peace. Once, when he found it, he saw that he was chosen for being a dutiful robot. While his friend was a havoc wrecker. He later asked Thor to take him back to Earth. Thor obliged but said that Bobby 1 had to give up life.       Thor sent Bobby 1 back to Earth by taking him to the transporter room. With a flash and a bang, Bobby was back on Earth, none the worse from the events. Joey 8 was soon taken to a mechanic after being found after the hurricane. They fixed him up and soon he was back up and running though he didn't ever again cause havoc. Bobby 1 soon found a new master to work for, and by chance, Joey 8 was there too. As they grew old and rickety together, they kept following orders, best of friends. Though Bobby 1 no longer had a life, he still remembered when he had one every time he looked up at the sky.

Item_Response: One Summer day in 2065 a boy named Brian was bored out of his mind. He tried to do something fun but he couldn't because he didn't have anybody to play with. So he tried to do something outside, whe he saw something coming down his street. When it came closer he knew it was a robot. The robot came up to Brian and said 'hi I am looking for a friend to play with, will you play with me?' Brian was so excited and said to the robot ' of course I will play with you, I have been looking for someone to play with me all day!' Brian said 'my name is Brian, what is your name?' The robot said' my name is playbot 2000 but you can call me playbot.'       Playbot and Brian played all day, they played tag, capture the flag, two hand touch football, and basketball. Brian was having so much fun. He was having so much fun he lost track of time. He said to Playbot 'I have to go in for dinner, can you play tomorrow?' Playbot's response was ' yes i can play, meet me tomorrow here at 11:30. Brian was okay with it and he went in for dinner. When he went in his mom asked him ' where have you been all day?' 'I have been playing with my new friend Playbot, he is a robot.' ' Oh, that is cool I have never had a robot play with me.' 'yeah mom it is cool, i am seeing him tomorrow outside at 11:30.' 'okay Brian thats fine but now you have to go to bed' 'okay mom, goodnight.'       The next day Brian shot out the door at 11:30. But he was shockrd not to see Playbot out there. But in five minutes Brian could see Playbot coming down the street. When Playbot came to Brian, Brian asked him 'why are you late?' Playbot said ' I slept to late.' Brian asked Robots sleep?' 'well we dont sleep like humans but we power down for 8-10 hours.' 'okay so lets go play now.' Another long day with Playbot. Brian is really tired. So Brian will go to bed a little earllyer than normal.       When Brian went outside the next day Playbot was already outside waiting for him. So Brian and Playbot make up a new game to play for the day. The game is called super tag. The rules are that it is regular tag but if you get taged you have 30 seconds to get the other person of your are out.

Item_Response: The End of His World    By: Kylie Burgess              One day I was walking down the sidewalk and boom! That's when it all went down hill, literally. Some thing a human, robot I don't know. Then that's when I realized it was a robot. The first word he said was 'hi' I did not know what to say but then it came out ' what are and what is your name'. He said my name is Dexter and I am a robot. I did not know what to do, so I ran home as fast as I could. But he followed me home and said why did you run. I stopped and thought.                   I was at school the next day and it was Dexter the robot our substitute teacher. So I thought and thought some more and i when I was done thinking. I told my self just keep my self together and I will be fine. We had a test that day so when we got them back at the the end of the day Dexter. I guess Dexter graded them and so I thought I did a good job but I failed my test. When my friend showed me her test she got an A+ we had the same exact answers. So I  accepted it and I would just talk to my teacher tomorrow. When I got home my mom wasn't home she usually is. But there he was a again in my house cooking food for me Dexter. I wasn't scared any more I was mad and that is when Dexter left my world forever and why I never say him again.

Item_Response: I woke up to what sounded like someone tapping on my window. Its 2:40 in the morning and there is a person outside my window. I started thinking about who it could be and why they were here and why they didn't just use the door. I got out of my bed and slowly approached my window. When I looked outside my window I didn't see anybody. I decided that I was just really tired and shrugged it off. A couple hours later around 5:00 in the morning I awoke to the same sound. I went over to my window again but found no one outside of it. I decided I must be really paranoid and went back to sleep.          The next morning I went downstairs and made myself breakfeast. I kept thinking back to last night when I heard tapping on my window. That really freaked me out. I finished my breakfeats and started getting ready for school when I heard this really annoying beeping sound from outside. I decided to just ignore it and finish getting read but after a couple minutes the noise still hadn't gone away. I went out into my backyard and started looking for the noise but I never found where it was coming from. I think I'm hearing things. I must be going crazy. I went back inside and finsihed getting ready for school. I decided to just forget about the noises and focus on my school work.                  After a really boring school day I walked all the way home. I went inside, grabbed a bowl of popcorn and went up to my room to start my homework. I walked into my room put my bag down and headed for my closet. I opended my closet and let out the loudest scream ever. I threw my popcorn bowl int he air and popcorn went flying everywhere. I started to slowly back up while starring at the object in my closet. After a couple of minutes I realised what it was. A robot. There was a robot in my closet. I starred at in shock for a couple minutes before slowly approaching it. It wasn't really big but it wasn't that small ethier. It had  arm and legs and it had a face. It was the color blue. My favorite. I slowly bent down and watched it crawl aound. After a couple minutes I picked it up and brought it to my bed.          Out of nowhere the robot started talking. I was shocked. Robots can talk?! It started telling me that it foud my house last night and was trying tog et in through the window but it was locked and that he was outside this morning watching me get ready for school and that all he wanted was a friend and a home. I decided to let the robot live with me and I named him  Andy. Andy the robot.               After a little while of talking to the robot it decided to go and charge it self while I decided to go make my self dinner.  I went downstairs and started cooking while thinking about todays events. I heard noises all through the night and I came home from school to see a robot in my closet. What weird day. At least I know what the noises where now. Turns out I'm not going crazy and I wasn't hearing things. After dinner was cooked I sat down and whatched a movie while I ate. After a little while the couch sunk down a little and I turned to see what it was. It was Andy. Andy my new friend. My new robot friend.

Item_Response: My Best Friend Steve            One autem day I was walking home from school. I have a hard life. I hated school. My parents don't even care about me anymore. All they do is work all day and all night at the robot labratory so now I have to fend for myself. Everyone at school hates me all because of how my life is planned out. I have no friends because everyone thinks that they are so perfect. Well their not. But this all ends. When I meet my new best friend Steve.            It was a beautiful Sunday morning. Birds chirping,sunlight shining through my window, the warmth hitting my face when I wake up. I could hear my parents downstairs coming home to see me until lunch. So I got up and headed downstairs for breakfest. I got suprised when I went downstairs because there was huge box sitting on the table. I thought to myself, 'What could it be...is it for me?' Then I got a huge hug from my dad and a little kiss on the cheek from mom. Then my dad said ' Sweetie we have been thinking, how lonely you are here at home without us here. So we got you a present! Come open it! I know you will love it.' So I began to walk over. I picked up the box and put it on my lap, grapped both the ends and opened it. I couldn't believe my eyes. It was my very own robot! ' Wow! Thanks! I'm going to name it Steve. '           ' Your welcome sweetie! Here, let me show you what it can do. ' So, he points to the camera. ' This is how it can see you. Its just like a pet. But better.' Then he points to the wheels. ' These wheels are al-terrain wheels. They can go on any surface. He is even water-proof!  You don't need to control him but we will need to program his name in. Why don't you do that.' So I picked him up,put the name in, and turned him on. He wasn't doing anything. Then Steve started to light up. It was amazing! The first thing he said was,'Hi! My name is Steve. ' Then I put him down. He started rolling around on the floor. He went all around the house( probably to analize it) and came back in a heart beat. Dang... he was fast.             After that day, we bacame real great friends. I could tell him anything and he would keep it a secret. But then something bad happened.            I was home alone because my parents were at work, I was making lunch for myself. I was making mac and cheese. I went to sit at the table and then something started burning. I looked over and the counter was on fire! So Steve and I ran over to try to stop it. But it was no use. So I went over to the phone to call 911 but didn't get there in time. The smoke got to my head and I fell to the ground. All I remember is Steve saving my life. He carried me carefully outside and away from the fire. Then he went back inside and put the fire out useing his fire extingquisher mode. Everything was ok. He came back to me and by that time I was awake. Steve was a true friend. He was family.            Today, Steve and I are the best of friends. He has been with me for about 5 years now. Even though my mom and dad weren't there for me through my life, Steve always was. He was like a parent. Steve truly was like an actual person. Like he was alive! I don't even look at him like hes a robot anymore. He is a real person in my eyes. Steve is my only family I have. He is my little protecter robot.

Item_Response: Have you ever seen Mr. Robot 'o on TV commercials and really wanted it because it looked cool? Well here's some advice.... don't get one! Imagine waiting all week for a toy robot and then finally getting it in the mail, but it doesn't at all live up to your expectations. Fortunately, the robot will do anything you want. Good so far right? Well, keep listening. Mr. Robot 'o will be you own personal servant doing anything you ask.... until you stop giving him attention. Then things go nuts! Here's the story:                      It was a beautiful Sunday morning. The sun was smiling and the birds were singing their lullaby in the trees. 'Hunnay, something came in the mail for you!' hollered my mom from downstairs. My eyes lit up like stars and my heart skipped a beat. I knew that it was the robot that I ordered online.                      Last week I saw a Mr. Robot 'o commercial that caught my attention right when I heard it was a robot that could do homework. It can do a lot of other things to including making you meals, picking out outfits for you, play any sport or game, and do your chores. I used the money I got from my birthday to buy it and I have been waiting for it all week.                     I rushed downstairs to see my toy, eager to finally have the amazing creation. When I got downstairs I saw the box sitting on the kitchen counter. I eagerly ripped it open, but then my heart sank. All that was in the box was a little robot about 6 inches tall. It was metal, as the commercial had said, but it was really cheap metal.                    'I paid $200.00 for this!' I exclaimed with unsatisfaction. 'I could've bought this at the 99 cent store!'  I crossed my arms and my face turned red. My mom heard my whining and came over to see what was wrong. I explained that it was nothing like the TV had said, but she told me to put in the batteries and see what it could do anyways. I did as she said and took the robot outside so if it could do anything, it would have space.                 'Mr.- Robot- 'o- here- what- can- I- do- for- you?' The robot stated.                  'Awww! This thing can't do anything but talk!' I moaned and my head dropped like a dying flower.                  'This- is- not- true- master- I- can- do- anything- you- want,' said the robot. My eyes grew big and my heart jumped back into place. The robot could understand me!                  'If you can do anything I want, then get bigger!' I told the robot. Suddenly the robot's arms and legs extended. It grew by the second and eventually became 3 feet tall! A smile spread from ear to ear across my face.                   'Is- this- good- master?' questioned the robot.                  'Great!' I replied.                   The rest of the day I had fun with my robot. It really could do anything you asked it to. I wanted to play soccer and a soccer ball popped right out of its stomach. I craved a bowl of my favorite type of ice cream and it came right out of its mouth. I decided not to tell my mom what the new robot could do because she would probably give me restrictions on it. But, that was a bad idea because the next day, things didn't go to well.                    Monday came, which meant school, and I had to leave   my robot for the day.                     'Bye robot! I will see you later!' I yelled while walking out the door with my little sister.                     'You- are- leaving- me?' It asked me, but I was already gone. That was when the bad things started. While I was gone the robot became angry because I had left it. It grew another foot and did some very bad things and then did something horrible!                       The school day went by and the whole day I thought about what me and Mr. Robot 'o were gonnna do after school. At the end of the day, while my class and I were packing up, the all call came on and asked for me to come to the office before dismissal. My eyebrows raised. I thought to myself, did I do anything bad today?                     When I got to the office, my little sister Paige, who is in kindergarten, was sitting in one of the chairs with tears dripping down her face. I hurried over to her and asked her what was wrong, but she was to upset to answer. I then walked up to the front desk to see why my sister was crying and why I was called here.                     'Do you know where your mom is?' asked Mrs. Jones, the front desk lady, who is not particularily nice. 'Because she didn't come to pick up Paige at 12 and now its 3!'                     'No, I don't, but Paige can just come with me because I walk home,' I stated. As we walked out of the school my heart started to pound wildly. 'What if my mom was in trouble? She is never late!' I thought to myself.                     'Where's mwommy??' asked Paige. She had stopped crying, now that she was comforted by me.                     'She is probably just at home, don't worry.' I replied, trying to keep her calm.                       When we got home, things were way different from this morning. There was trash everywhere and the chairs and tables were knocked down. The TV was broken and there was water all over the ground. Paige clung onto me and began crying again. My heart stopped and I froze like a statue. I didn't know what to do. 'Was there a burgler?' I thought to myself, but then suddenly I knew the answer. On the box that Mr. Robot 'o came in there was writing. It said: You shouldn't have left me. My legs began shaking and a million thoughts rotated around my head.                  'Sissy, where is mwommy?' Paige asked again and this time I replied with I don't know. I realized that the first thing I needed to do was find Mr. Robot 'o and break him, so he couldn't do anymore bad things. 'Bam!!' a sound came from upstairs and at that moment I knew Mr. Robot 'o had taken my mom. I then saw the bat that I used to play baseball with Mr. Robot 'o the day before and got an idea.  I grabbed Paige's hand and we both slowly tip toed upstairs.                     'You- should- not- have- let- her- leave- me.' stated the robot to my mom and I knew that was the time for my move.                    'Stay here and don't move!' I told Paige and she nodded. I continued to the top of the stairs, cut around the corner, and saw that the robot had my mom in the closet. I hesitated and didn't know if I should have stuck with my plan, but then made my decision. I sprinted towards them and came right behind the robot then hit it in the head with the baseball bat. It fell to the ground and I took out its batteries. My mom had ductape over her mouth and I ripped it off then gave her a big hug. I grabbed the lifeless robot and took him outside, then threw him in the trashcan.                   'I am so proud of you!' stated my mom.                   'What a waste of 200 bucks huh,' I stated with a laugh.

Item_Response: One late summer evening, Lucas and his friends, Mary and Jones, were playing outside when they heard a noise. They all went running towards the woods. In the woods they saw a small, alien like device that was beeping. It was gray and had eyes that were closed. It almost looked like a human. They touched it, curiosity getting the better of them. All of the sudden, it turned on and looked at them. They were terrified!         The small robot sat up and and spoke in a weird voice, ' I am Jrew, a robot that helps animals in need. It seems that I am lost. I fell out of the back of a transporting truck and broke my arm.' He sounded worried, but the kids knew that he wasn't in pain. Lucas, Mary and Jones helped the robot up and went inside to bandage his arm. Luckily, nobody saw Jrew so he was safe. If anybody saw him, they would be scared, maybe even brake him. The kids didn't know what to do with him. They didn't know where Jrew was heading or where he came from.           When Lucas' mom got home, he told her all about Jrew. His mom was a scientist and knew the company that had founded Jrew. She gave the company a call and they came and got him. Lucas, Mary and Jones were sad to see him go but where happy to know that he was alright and doing a good deed.

Item_Response: I have always anted to build a robot. So two months ago, I did. He was silver, and was about 5 feet 7 inches. In my mind he could do my homework and do my chores, but I knew he would never come to life. I couldn't have been more wrong.              It took me two weeks to build my robot. He wasn't going to have a name, he was just going to be a fragment of my imagination, of course he would be sitting up in my bedroom doing nothing because he wasn't programed to do anything. I never thought he would be literally sitting up in my bedroom, ready to talk to me. But I guess anything can happen.              I went to school the day after I had finished my robot(it had been winter break, so there wasn't school when he was being built.) I was excited to see all my friends again, and to be back to my normal routine. School was boring like usual so I couldn't wait to get home and sit onb my couch.              As soon as I got home, I ran up to my room, and started my homework, which I actually never finnished that day. While I was doing my homework, something from behind me asked,'Don't you want me to do that for you?' I turned around. That voice I had only heard in my head while I was building my robot. When I saw what was behind me, I freaked out. It was my robot, sitting in the corner of my bedroom staring at me with his silver glowing eyes. He was actually alive! I couldn't beliueve it. I said,'Sure, since that is what you are programed to do, I guess.' He laughed in a strange, but friendly way. 'I am not sure what my name is, but I can do your homework, and by the way, while you were at school I made your bed and did the dishes.' he said. 'Well I don't have a name for you so I guess it can be what I have been calling you 'Robot,''I said awkwardly.              The garage door went up, and I heard my mom screaming 'I'm home.' I walked down the stairs. 'Hi mom,' I said,'Anything weird happening today?' She shook her head. She walked into the kitchen, and walked back out with a smile on her face. 'You did your chores!' she said excited. 'Yeah I guess so,' I said. I ran upstairs.               My window was wide open. My robot was gone. My homework was not done. My heart raced.                'Mom, where is my robot?' I screamed. 'What robot?' she asked. I sat down on my bed. Had I really imagined the whole thing? No. I couldn't have. He was there. He had to be. My window being open was just a coincidence. It had to be. He had to be in the corner of my room, sitting there, not programed, not doing my homework, but just a lifeless robot. He was there. I knew cause I saw the glint of his eyes watching me in the dark light. I had told my mom about the robot and even showed her it when I was finnished. How could she not remember? I didn't know, and I didn't ever find out.

Item_Response: Hi, my name is Donny.  I have a robot.  It's not as great as it sounds.  Trust me.  His name is Rodrick and he is not very smart at all.         Sometimes I wish that stupid thing would just shut-up.  I guess I better tell you whats wrong with him.  Number one he looks like a big rusty hunk of metal. Number two his eyes flicker and they are red so it's hard to fall asleep.  Can you imagine two flashing red things the size of a baseball staring at you all night.  Lastly, his dang smoke detector has a low battery so it beeps every five minutes.  The bad thing is they don't make that kind of battery any more and it never dies because he runs on solar power.        I figured I would take him to a mechanic or something.  When I got there the guy said what the heck is that piece of crap.  Fortinatly my Mom took me because my Dad built it.  I said it's a working piece of crap, it just has a lot of problems.  He said he didn't know anything about it so I asked him

Item_Response: The Greatest Invention to Man-Kind                On a cold bitter day in Portland Oregon a boy named Ja'von thought that he would be an inventor when he groes up. Ja'von was a 16 year old inventor. Ja'von has never invented something amazing like a car, hellicopter, computer or a microwave. Ja'von has invented pots for plants that keep the water in it for over a week, without the plant needing water. Ja'von always wanted to build a car that fits 7 people that runs on a triple A battery. Ja'von and his family did not have the money to buy parts to a car for him to operate on.                  The years went on and Ja'von still has not built that car. On a warm day Ja'von recieved some mail. His mail was a letter from Stanford University. It basiclly told him that he was offered a schoolarship if he wanted it. The schoolarship was for Electrical Sciencie. Ja'von took the schoolarship even even though he was offered a schoolarship to University of Yale, University of Harvard and University of Oregon. The weeks went by and Ja'von finally had the chance to invent something. Ja'von had the Sciencie teacher in the world in his opinion. His sciencie teacher's name was Mrs.Brandz. Mrs.Brandz assigned an assignment that would change the world.                    Mrs.Branz told them that they had to make a one of a kind invention. She told them that they could buy thier own stuff and she would have supplies for them to use. Ja'von knew he did not want to do a car, that he had wanted to build since he was 16 years old. So he came up with the idea of a robot. So when he got back to his Dorm Rroom Ja'von started drawing up 1,000's of some idea's. With all the 1,000's of crumbled piecies of paper he threw into the trash can. He finally found an idea. His Robot was called the  H.D.R 7. The H.D.R 7 stood for Handy Dandy Robot 7. Two weeeks later Ja'von was finished with the H.D.R 7. Ja'von presentated his invention to the class. His classmates were absouleley amazed. Mrs.Branz entered Ja'von into the College Inventors Program. This was for the best inventors for each state. Ja'von came in 2nd place. Although his invention was the most bought invention in 2016. Ja'von later went on to win a Noble Peace Prize. When he turned 68 years old.
